{"type":"tool_execution_end","toolCallId":"call_8EtEg4WqZrfGSwtJ92gzZc57|fc_09e1a19d9e220e560169de0a0886f0819a9fb8f6ed8c7a5f0b","toolName":"read","result":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Plan Review\n\nReview implementation plans for quality, completeness, and feasibility. Plans MUST target AI execution and follow progressive disclosure.\n\n## Target Paths\n- `.agents/tasks/<id>/plan.md`\n- `.agents/tasks/<id>/stages/*.md`\n\n## Plan-Specific Rules\n\n### Look For\n- **Deviations**: Plan deviates from the initial `spec`. Confirm plan is aligned with `plan.md` frontmatter `spec` property.\n- **Bloat**: Remove tool explanations, verbose procedures (\"I will now...\"), and discoverable context.\n- **Gaps**: Missing prerequisites, incomplete success criteria, or undocumented assumptions.\n- **Inconsistencies**: Conflicting instructions between stages, mismatched dependencies, or naming drift.\n- **Assumptions**: Hardcoded values without context, implicit state, or missing environment variables.\n- **Bad Testing**: Tests SHOULD be efficient. NO brittle or flaky tests. Tests SHOULD NOT be redundant.\n- **Optimizations**: Parallelizable steps, redundant I/O, missing tool preferences.\n- **Dependency Bloat**: \"Depends On\" lists stages not referenced or tested in instructions.\n\n### Test Review\nWhen reviewing planned tests, test strategy, coverage quality, brittleness, or validation design, use the `quality-engineer` skill.\n\n### Auto-fix Guidelines\n- **Remove**: \"npm install\", \"run command\", tool tutorials, conditional explanations.\n- **Simplify**: Procedures -> outcomes, multi-step -> single action.\n- **Prefer**: Existing tools (Read/Edit/Grep) over generic bash commands.\n- **Cleanup**: Remove stages not referenced or tested in stage instructions.\n"}]},"isError":false}
