{"type":"message_start","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_IZWJbRfzqclvIdHG3Fom6OTa|fc_09e1a19d9e220e560169de0a6e2c40819abaf0fde47ee9f581","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Progress: refactor-agnostic\n\n## Status checklist\n- [x] Task scaffold created under `.agents/tasks/refactor-agnostic`\n- [x] Restructure scope + architecture captured\n- [x] Draft concrete module/file move plan against current `index.ts`\n- [ ] Implement `multicodex-core` extraction (first pass)\n- [ ] Rewire existing pi extension to use core\n- [ ] Add regression tests for parity\n- [ ] (Optional) Add gateway prototype for Mnemos integration\n\n## Current notes\n- This task is focused on architecture + extraction planning first.\n- Keep behavior parity while reducing pi-specific coupling.\n- The detailed implementation plan now exists in `plan.md` with stage-level instructions.\n\n## Next step\nBegin Stage 1: extract pure helpers and shared types, then follow the staged rollout in order.\n\n## Review\n- What's correct\n  - The spec matches the current README/code on the documented command surface (`/multicodex-login`, `/multicodex-use`, `/multicodex-status`), the selection heuristic shape, the usage cache/retry constants, and the thin-adapter target.\n- Fixed: Issue and resolution\n  - Captured the main blocking mismatches for follow-up: context docs still mention `/multicodex-switch` and require a non-pi consumer, while the spec/code currently target `/multicodex-use` and treat the gateway spike as optional.\n- Note: Observations\n  - Token refresh deduplication, widened public interfaces, and reference-implementation storage migration are not all part of the current code contract, so the spec should mark them as explicit scope additions or narrow them.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776159342175}}
