non-pi validation and parity regression coverage\n    28\t  - Instructions: [add-non-pi-validation-and-parity-regression-coverage.md](./stages/add-non-pi-validation-and-parity-regression-coverage.md)\n    29\t  - Depends On: 3\n    30\t\n    31\t## Dependency rationale\n    32\t- Stage 1 must land first because the selection, usage, and retry helpers are the pure seams that every later core module imports.\n    33\t- Stage 2 depends on Stage 1 because the state manager should be assembled on top of the extracted helpers and shared types, not by re-implementing them.\n    34\t- Stage 3 depends on Stage 2 because the pi adapter should become a thin consumer of the new core manager, storage adapter, and usage/token collaborators.\n    35\t- Stage 4 depends on Stage 3 because the final parity sweep should validate both the non-pi core reuse path and the adapter/root compatibility surface after the rewiring is complete.\n    36\t\n    37\t## Risks and edge cases\n    38\t- Storage migration must preserve the current legacy `~/.pi/agent/multicodex.json` shape while still writing a canonical versioned schema once the core loads it.\n    39\t- The reference implementationâ€™s lower-usage tie-breaker must not leak into the current selection policy unless tests/docs explicitly opt into it.\n    40\t- Manual account selection should stay session-local; do not persist adapter-only session overrides into storage.\n    41\t- Token refresh deduplication is an optional enhancement, not a required parity behavior, so it should not block the core extraction.\n    42\t- Adapter-specific browser launch failures must remain warnings, not hard crashes, in environments without an openable browser.\n\n--- stage1 ---\n     1\t---\n     2\tplan_id: refactor-agnostic\n     3\ttitle: extract pure helpers and shared types\n     4\tstatus: idle\n     5\tupdated: 2026-04-14T00:00:00Z\n     6\t---\n     7\t\n     8\tExtract the quota, usage, retry, and account-selection helpers into platform-agnostic modules with no pi runtime imports.\n     9\t\n    10\t## Steps\n    11\t- [ ] Create `core/types.ts` and move the shared data model there: `Account`, `StorageData`, and the canonical persisted account fields used by selection and persistence.\n    12\t- [ ] Create `core/errors.ts` and move `isQuotaErrorMessage`, `getErrorMessage`, `isAbortLikeError`, `getUsageHttpStatus`, and `isRetryableUsageError` into it.\n    13\t- [ ] Create `core/retry.ts` and move `sleepWithSignal` into it unchanged in behavior.\n    14\t- [ ] Create `core/usage.ts` and move `CodexUsageSnapshot`, `normalizeUsedPercent`, `normalizeResetAt`, `parseUsageWindow`, `parseCodexUsageResponse`, `isUsageUntouched`, `getNextResetAt`, and `getWeeklyResetAt` into it.\n    15\t- [ ] Create `core/selection.ts` and move `isAccountAvailable`, `pickRandomAccount`, `pickEarliestWeeklyResetAccount`, and `pickBestAccount` into it.\n    16\t- [ ] Create `core/index.ts` as a barrel that re-exports the current root-stable helper surface from the new core modules.\n    17\t- [ ] Keep `formatResetAt` out of core; it belongs in the pi adapter because it is presentation logic, not domain logic.\n    18\t- [ ] Split the current helper assertions out of `index.test.ts` into focused core tests that import only `core/*` modules.\n    19\t- [ ] Update the root `index.ts` to re-export the moved helper names through the new barrel without changing behavior.\n    20\t\n    21\t## Success Criteria\n    22\t- [ ] `core/*` modules can be imported without `@mariozechner/pi-ai` or `@mariozechner/pi-coding-agent`.\n    23\t- [ ] Unit coverage exists for quota classification, usage parsing/reset conversion, untouched-usage detection, and selection heuristics.\n    24\t- [ ] The root compatibility surface still exports `isQuotaErrorMessage`, `parseCodexUsageResponse`, `isUsageUntouched`, `getNextResetAt`, `getWeeklyResetAt`, and `pickBestAccount`.\n    25\t- [ ] No observable behavior changes for selection, parsing, or retry classification.\n\n--- stage2 ---\n"}],"details":{}}}
