ification.\n\n--- stage2 ---\n     1\t---\n     2\tplan_id: refactor-agnostic\n     3\ttitle: extract core state manager and storage\n     4\tstatus: idle\n     5\tupdated: 2026-04-14T00:00:00Z\n     6\t---\n     7\t\n     8\tMove persistence, usage refresh, token refresh, cooldown bookkeeping, and account activation into `multicodex-core` behind injected collaborators.\n     9\t\n    10\t## Steps\n    11\t- [ ] Create `core/storage.ts` and define the platform-agnostic persistence contract: load/save adapter, canonical storage schema, and migration helpers for the legacy unversioned `{ accounts, activeEmail? }` file.\n    12\t- [ ] Create `core/usage-client.ts` and move `fetchCodexUsage` into an injectable client that accepts the access token, optional account id, and abort signal while preserving timeout and retry semantics.\n    13\t- [ ] Create `core/account-manager.ts` and move the stateful account manager behavior there: load/save, active/manual resolution, usage cache, usage refresh, selection activation, token validity, token refresh, and quota exhaustion handling.\n    14\t- [ ] Keep the manager API compatible with the current adapter needs: `getAccounts`, `getAccount`, `getActiveAccount`, `getManualAccount`, `hasManualAccount`, `getAvailableManualAccount`, `setActiveAccount`, `setManualAccount`, `clearManualAccount`, `addOrUpdateAccount`, `getCachedUsage`, `refreshUsageForAccount`, `refreshUsageForAllAccounts`, `refreshUsageIfStale`, `activateBestAccount`, `ensureValidToken`, and `handleQuotaExceeded`.\n    15\t- [ ] Inject the storage adapter, token refresher, usage client, clock, random source, and warning callback instead of hard-coding filesystem or pi APIs inside the manager.\n    16\t- [ ] Preserve the current usage cache TTL, retry policy, token freshness threshold, and quota cooldown fallback exactly unless tests/docs explicitly change them.\n    17\t- [ ] Add migration tests that load the current legacy storage file, normalize it to the canonical schema, and verify the written-back result is idempotent.\n    18\t- [ ] Add deterministic tests for cache hits, bounded retry/backoff, abort-like failures returning cached data, expired-token refresh, and quota cooldown marking.\n    19\t- [ ] Keep manual account selection session-local; do not persist manual overrides as part of storage migration.\n    20\t\n    21\t## Success Criteria\n    22\t- [ ] The core manager no longer imports node filesystem modules or pi runtime APIs directly.\n    23\t- [ ] Legacy storage loads successfully and saves back in the canonical versioned shape without losing valid account records.\n    24\t- [ ] The cache TTL, retry backoff, token refresh threshold, and cooldown behavior all match the current behavior contract.\n    25\t- [ ] The new core tests cover migration, refresh, cache, and cooldown behavior with injected fakes.\n\n--- stage3 ---\n     1\t---\n     2\tplan_id: refactor-agnostic\n     3\ttitle: rewire pi adapter and compatibility barrel\n     4\tstatus: idle\n     5\tupdated: 2026-04-14T00:00:00Z\n     6\t---\n     7\t\n     8\tMove pi-specific wiring out of the monolith so the adapter becomes a thin integration layer over the new core modules.\n     9\t\n    10\t## Steps\n    11\t- [ ] Create `adapter/pi/storage.ts` to own the default `~/.pi/agent/multicodex.json` path and implement the core storage interface using `node:fs`, `node:path`, and `node:os`.\n    12\t- [ ] Create `adapter/pi/oauth.ts` and move `resolveCodexOAuthFns`, `loginOpenAICodexCompat`, and `refreshOpenAICodexTokenCompat` there.\n    13\t- [ ] Create `adapter/pi/browser.ts` and move `openLoginInBrowser` there, keeping browser-open failures as warnings.\n    14\t- [ ] Create `adapter/pi/stream-utils.ts` and move `createErrorAssistantMessage`, `withProvider`, `createLinkedAbortController`, and `createTimeoutController` there.\n    15\t- [ ] Create `adapter/pi/status.ts` and move `formatResetAt` there.\n    16\t- [ ] Create `adapter/pi/provider.ts` and move `getOpenAICodexMirror` plus `buildMulticodexProviderConfig` there.\n    17\t- [ ] Create `adapter/pi/stream-wrapper.ts` and move `createStreamWrapper` there, preserving header injection, provider-id rewriting, quota-before-output rotation, and the bounded retry loop.\n    18\t- [ ] Create `adapter/pi/commands.ts` and move the `/multicodex-login`, `/multicodex-use`, and `/multicodex-status` handlers there without changing the user-visible strings or menu flow.\n    19\t- [ ] Create `adapter/pi/hooks.ts` and move the `session_start` and `session_switch` orchestration there.\n    20\t- [ ] Create `adapter/pi/index.ts` as the default extension entrypoint that wires the core manager, pi storage adapter, provider registration, commands, hooks, and warning routing together.\n    21\t- [ ] Update the root `index.ts` to act as a compatibility barrel and default-export shim that preserves the existing public names, including `Account`, `AccountManager`, `CodexUsageSnapshot`, `ProviderModelDef`, `buildMulticodexProviderConfig`, `createStreamWrapper`, `getNextResetAt`, `getOpenAICodexMirror`, `getWeeklyResetAt`, `isQuotaErrorMessage`, `isUsageUntouched`, `parseCodexUsageResponse`, `pickBestAccount`, and the default pi extension function.\n    22\t- [ ] Keep provider registration defensive: if `openai-codex-responses` is unavailable, warn and skip registration rather than crashing startup.\n    23\t- [ ] Move the adapter-focused assertions out of `index.test.ts` into dedicated pi-adapter tests for provider mirroring, manual selection, stream rotation, and event translation.\n    24\t\n    25\t## Success Criteria\n    26\t- [ ] The pi adapter owns all pi-specific API usage and the core tree remains pi-free.\n    27\t- [ ] The documented command surface and current output strings remain unchanged.\n    28\t- [ ] The provider still mirrors `openai-codex` metadata, and stream events still come back with the caller-facing provider id.\n    29\t- [ ] Root imports used by the current tests still resolve through the compatibility barrel.\n\n--- stage4 ---\n     1\t---\n     2\tplan_id: refactor-agnostic\n     3\ttitle: add non-pi validation and parity regression coverage\n     4\tstatus: idle\n     5\tupdated: 2026-04-14T00:00:00Z\n     6\t---\n     7\t\n     8\tProve the extracted core works without pi runtime imports, then finish the regression sweep by moving the remaining behavioral assertions into focused module tests.\n     9\t\n    10\t## Steps\n    11\t- [ ] Add one non-pi validation path that imports only `core/*` and exercises selection, refresh, caching, and quota handling with fake storage, fake token refresh, and fake usage fetch collaborators.\n    12\t- [ ] Keep the validation lightweight: a Vitest suite or small smoke harness is enough as long as it proves the core can be used without `@mariozechner/pi-coding-agent`.\n    13\t- [ ] Split the remaining assertions from `index.test.ts` into module-focused tests so root coverage can shrink to a compatibility smoke test.\n    14\t- [ ] Preserve the parity contract in tests for manual account precedence, usage parsing, untouched detection, cached usage refresh, token refresh threshold, quota-before-output rotation, and quota-after-output non-retry behavior.\n    15\t- [ ] Add or update README notes only as needed to explain the internal core/adapter split while keeping the public pi command surface unchanged.\n    16\t- [ ] Run the full validation matrix at the end of the rollout: `npm run lint`, `npm run tsgo`, and `npm run test`.\n    17\t\n    18\t## Success Criteria\n    19\t- [ ] At least one validation path imports the extracted core without pi runtime packages.\n    20\t- [ ] The regression suite covers the full behavior parity contract from the spec.\n    21\t- [ ] The root compatibility tests are reduced to a small smoke layer that proves the legacy exports and entrypoint still work.\n    22\t- [ ] The repository documentation still describes the same user-visible commands and behavior.\n    23\t- [ ] All checks pass.\n"}],"details":{}}}
{"type":"tool_execution_end","toolCallId":"call_0sfaZgtJw5VNcEU8ZUDKguY2|fc_09e1a19d9e220e560169de0ad03788819abdf79d888a3ab5cd","toolName":"bash","result":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"     1\t---\n     2\tid: refactor-agnostic\n     3\tspec: .agents/tasks/refactor-agnostic/spec.md\n     4\tstatus: ready\n     5\tupdated: 2026-04-14T00:00:00Z\n     6\t---\n     7\t\n     8\tExtract a platform-agnostic `multicodex-core` from the monolith, then rewire the pi adapter around it without changing the documented user-facing surface.\n     9\t\n    10\t## Stages\n    11\t- [ ] Stage 1:\n    12\t  - Title: Extract pure helpers and shared types\n    13\t  - Instructions: [extract-pure-helpers-and-shared-types.md](./stages/extract-pure-helpers-and-shared-types.md)\n    14\t  - Depends On: none\n    15\t\n    16\t- [ ] Stage 2:\n    17\t  - Title: Extract core state manager and storage\n    18\t  - Instructions: [extract-core-state-manager-and-storage.md](./stages/extract-core-state-manager-and-storage.md)\n    19\t  - Depends On: 1\n    20\t\n    21\t- [ ] Stage 3:\n    22\t  - Title: Rewire pi adapter and compatibility barrel\n    23\t  - Instructions: [rewire-pi-adapter-and-compatibility-barrel.md](./stages/rewire-pi-adapter-and-compatibility-barrel.md)\n    24\t  - Depends On: 2\n    25\t\n    26\t- [ ] Stage 4:\n    27\t  - Title: Add non-pi validation and parity regression coverage\n    28\t  - Instructions: [add-non-pi-validation-and-parity-regression-coverage.md](./stages/add-non-pi-validation-and-parity-regression-coverage.md)\n    29\t  - Depends On: 3\n    30\t\n    31\t## Dependency rationale\n    32\t- Stage 1 must land first because the selection, usage, and retry helpers are the pure seams that every later core module imports.\n    33\t- Stage 2 depends on Stage 1 because the state manager should be assembled on top of the extracted helpers and shared types, not by re-implementing them.\n    34\t- Stage 3 depends on Stage 2 because the pi adapter should become a thin consumer of the new core manager, storage adapter, and usage/token collaborators.\n    35\t- Stage 4 depends on Stage 3 because the final parity sweep should validate both the non-pi core reuse path and the adapter/root compatibility surface after the rewiring is complete.\n    36\t\n    37\t## Risks and edge cases\n    38\t- Storage migration must preserve the current legacy `~/.pi/agent/multicodex.json` shape while still writing a canonical versioned schema once the core loads it.\n    39\t- The reference implementationâ€™s lower-usage tie-breaker must not leak into the current selection policy unless tests/docs explicitly opt into it.\n    40\t- Manual account selection should stay session-local; do not persist adapter-only session overrides into storage.\n    41\t- Token refresh deduplication is an optional enhancement, not a required parity behavior, so it should not block the core extraction.\n    42\t- Adapter-specific browser launch failures must remain warnings, not hard crashes, in environments without an openable browser.\n\n--- stage1 ---\n     1\t---\n     2\tplan_id: refactor-agnostic\n     3\ttitle: extract pure helpers and shared types\n     4\tstatus: idle\n     5\tupdated: 2026-04-14T00:00:00Z\n     6\t---\n     7\t\n     8\tExtract the quota, usage, retry, and account-selection helpers into platform-agnostic modules with no pi runtime imports.\n     9\t\n    10\t## Steps\n    11\t- [ ] Create `core/types.ts` and move the shared data model there: `Account`, `StorageData`, and the canonical persisted account fields used by selection and persistence.\n    12\t- [ ] Create `core/errors.ts` and move `isQuotaErrorMessage`, `getErrorMessage`, `isAbortLikeError`, `getUsageHttpStatus`, and `isRetryableUsageError` into it.\n    13\t- [ ] Create `core/retry.ts` and move `sleepWithSignal` into it unchanged in behavior.\n    14\t- [ ] Create `core/usage.ts` and move `CodexUsageSnapshot`, `normalizeUsedPercent`, `normalizeResetAt`, `parseUsageWindow`, `parseCodexUsageResponse`, `isUsageUntouched`, `getNextResetAt`, and `getWeeklyResetAt` into it.\n    15\t- [ ] Create `core/selection.ts` and move `isAccountAvailable`, `pickRandomAccount`, `pickEarliestWeeklyResetAccount`, and `pickBestAccount` into it.\n    16\t- [ ] Create `core/index.ts` as a barrel that re-exports the current root-stable helper surface from the new core modules.\n    17\t- [ ] Keep `formatResetAt` out of core; it belongs in the pi adapter because it is presentation logic, not domain logic.\n    18\t- [ ] Split the current helper assertions out of `index.test.ts` into focused core tests that import only `core/*` modules.\n    19\t- [ ] Update the root `index.ts` to re-export the moved helper names through the new barrel without changing behavior.\n    20\t\n    21\t## Success Criteria\n    22\t- [ ] `core/*` modules can be imported without `@mariozechner/pi-ai` or `@mariozechner/pi-coding-agent`.\n    23\t- [ ] Unit coverage exists for quota classification, usage parsing/reset conversion, untouched-usage detection, and selection heuristics.\n    24\t- [ ] The root compatibility surface still exports `isQuotaErrorMessage`, `parseCodexUsageResponse`, `isUsageUntouched`, `getNextResetAt`, `getWeeklyResetAt`, and `pickBestAccount`.\n    25\t- [ ] No observable behavior changes for selection, parsing, or retry classification.\n\n--- stage2 ---\n     1\t---\n     2\tplan_id: refactor-agnostic\n     3\ttitle: extract core state manager and storage\n     4\tstatus: idle\n     5\tupdated: 2026-04-14T00:00:00Z\n     6\t---\n     7\t\n     8\tMove persistence, usage refresh, token refresh, cooldown bookkeeping, and account activation into `multicodex-core` behind injected collaborators.\n     9\t\n    10\t## Steps\n    11\t- [ ] Create `core/storage.ts` and define the platform-agnostic persistence contract: load/save adapter, canonical storage schema, and migration helpers for the legacy unversioned `{ accounts, activeEmail? }` file.\n    12\t- [ ] Create `core/usage-client.ts` and move `fetchCodexUsage` into an injectable client that accepts the access token, optional account id, and abort signal while preserving timeout and retry semantics.\n    13\t- [ ] Create `core/account-manager.ts` and move the stateful account manager behavior there: load/save, active/manual resolution, usage cache, usage refresh, selection activation, token validity, token refresh, and quota exhaustion handling.\n    14\t- [ ] Keep the manager API compatible with the current adapter needs: `getAccounts`, `getAccount`, `getActiveAccount`, `getManualAccount`, `hasManualAccount`, `getAvailableManualAccount`, `setActiveAccount`, `setManualAccount`, `clearManualAccount`, `addOrUpdateAccount`, `getCachedUsage`, `refreshUsageForAccount`, `refreshUsageForAllAccounts`, `refreshUsageIfStale`, `activateBestAccount`, `ensureValidToken`, and `handleQuotaExceeded`.\n    15\t- [ ] Inject the storage adapter, token refresher, usage client, clock, random source, and warning callback instead of hard-coding filesystem or pi APIs inside the manager.\n    16\t- [ ] Preserve the current usage cache TTL, retry policy, token freshness threshold, and quota cooldown fallback exactly unless tests/docs explicitly change them.\n    17\t- [ ] Add migration tests that load the current legacy storage file, normalize it to the canonical schema, and verify the written-back result is idempotent.\n    18\t- [ ] Add deterministic tests for cache hits, bounded retry/backoff, abort-like failures returning cached data, expired-token refresh, and quota cooldown marking.\n    19\t- [ ] Keep manual account selection session-local; do not persist manual overrides as part of storage migration.\n    20\t\n    21\t## Success Criteria\n    22\t- [ ] The core manager no longer imports node filesystem modules or pi runtime APIs directly.\n    23\t- [ ] Legacy storage loads successfully and saves back in the canonical versioned shape without losing valid account records.\n    24\t- [ ] The cache TTL, retry backoff, token refresh threshold, and cooldown behavior all match the current behavior contract.\n    25\t- [ ] The new core tests cover migration, refresh, cache, and cooldown behavior with injected fakes.\n\n--- stage3 ---\n     1\t---\n     2\tplan_id: refactor-agnostic\n     3\ttitle: rewire pi adapter and compatibility barrel\n     4\tstatus: idle\n     5\tupdated: 2026-04-14T00:00:00Z\n     6\t---\n     7\t\n     8\tMove pi-specific wiring out of the monolith so the adapter becomes a thin integration layer over the new core modules.\n     9\t\n    10\t## Steps\n    11\t- [ ] Create `adapter/pi/storage.ts` to own the default `~/.pi/agent/multicodex.json` path and implement the core storage interface using `node:fs`, `node:path`, and `node:os`.\n    12\t- [ ] Create `adapter/pi/oauth.ts` and move `resolveCodexOAuthFns`, `loginOpenAICodexCompat`, and `refreshOpenAICodexTokenCompat` there.\n    13\t- [ ] Create `adapter/pi/browser.ts` and move `openLoginInBrowser` there, keeping browser-open failures as warnings.\n    14\t- [ ] Create `adapter/pi/stream-utils.ts` and move `createErrorAssistantMessage`, `withProvider`, `createLinkedAbortController`, and `createTimeoutController` there.\n    15\t- [ ] Create `adapter/pi/status.ts` and move `formatResetAt` there.\n    16\t- [ ] Create `adapter/pi/provider.ts` and move `getOpenAICodexMirror` plus `buildMulticodexProviderConfig` there.\n    17\t- [ ] Create `adapter/pi/stream-wrapper.ts` and move `createStreamWrapper` there, preserving header injection, provider-id rewriting, quota-before-output rotation, and the bounded retry loop.\n    18\t- [ ] Create `adapter/pi/commands.ts` and move the `/multicodex-login`, `/multicodex-use`, and `/multicodex-status` handlers there without changing the user-visible strings or menu flow.\n    19\t- [ ] Create `adapter/pi/hooks.ts` and move the `session_start` and `session_switch` orchestration there.\n    20\t- [ ] Create `adapter/pi/index.ts` as the default extension entrypoint that wires the core manager, pi storage adapter, provider registration, commands, hooks, and warning routing together.\n    21\t- [ ] Update the root `index.ts` to act as a compatibility barrel and default-export shim that preserves the existing public names, including `Account`, `AccountManager`, `CodexUsageSnapshot`, `ProviderModelDef`, `buildMulticodexProviderConfig`, `createStreamWrapper`, `getNextResetAt`, `getOpenAICodexMirror`, `getWeeklyResetAt`, `isQuotaErrorMessage`, `isUsageUntouched`, `parseCodexUsageResponse`, `pickBestAccount`, and the default pi extension function.\n    22\t- [ ] Keep provider registration defensive: if `openai-codex-responses` is unavailable, warn and skip registration rather than crashing startup.\n    23\t- [ ] Move the adapter-focused assertions out of `index.test.ts` into dedicated pi-adapter tests for provider mirroring, manual selection, stream rotation, and event translation.\n    24\t\n    25\t## Success Criteria\n    26\t- [ ] The pi adapter owns all pi-specific API usage and the core tree remains pi-free.\n    27\t- [ ] The documented command surface and current output strings remain unchanged.\n    28\t- [ ] The provider still mirrors `openai-codex` metadata, and stream events still come back with the caller-facing provider id.\n    29\t- [ ] Root imports used by the current tests still resolve through the compatibility barrel.\n\n--- stage4 ---\n     1\t---\n     2\tplan_id: refactor-agnostic\n     3\ttitle: add non-pi validation and parity regression coverage\n     4\tstatus: idle\n     5\tupdated: 2026-04-14T00:00:00Z\n     6\t---\n     7\t\n     8\tProve the extracted core works without pi runtime imports, then finish the regression sweep by moving the remaining behavioral assertions into focused module tests.\n     9\t\n    10\t## Steps\n    11\t- [ ] Add one non-pi validation path that imports only `core/*` and exercises selection, refresh, caching, and quota handling with fake storage, fake token refresh, and fake usage fetch collaborators.\n    12\t- [ ] Keep the validation lightweight: a Vitest suite or small smoke harness is enough as long as it proves the core can be used without `@mariozechner/pi-coding-agent`.\n    13\t- [ ] Split the remaining assertions from `index.test.ts` into module-focused tests so root coverage can shrink to a compatibility smoke test.\n    14\t- [ ] Preserve the parity contract in tests for manual account precedence, usage parsing, untouched detection, cached usage refresh, token refresh threshold, quota-before-output rotation, and quota-after-output non-retry behavior.\n    15\t- [ ] Add or update README notes only as needed to explain the internal core/adapter split while keeping the public pi command surface unchanged.\n    16\t- [ ] Run the full validation matrix at the end of the rollout: `npm run lint`, `npm run tsgo`, and `npm run test`.\n    17\t\n    18\t## Success Criteria\n    19\t- [ ] At least one validation path imports the extracted core without pi runtime packages.\n    20\t- [ ] The regression suite covers the full behavior parity contract from the spec.\n    21\t- [ ] The root compatibility tests are reduced to a small smoke layer that proves the legacy exports and entrypoint still work.\n    22\t- [ ] The repository documentation still describes the same user-visible commands and behavior.\n    23\t- [ ] All checks pass.\n"}]},"isError":false}
