{"type":"tool_execution_update","toolCallId":"call_bCAW8Oj1ytwWlsMIBKucn0tf|fc_09e1a19d9e220e560169de0ad88854819abd96cdcc2d83fcb6","toolName":"bash","args":{"command":"cd /home/linkdevk/repos/kg-multicodex && nl -ba .agents/tasks/refactor-agnostic/spec.md | sed -n '320,460p'","timeout":10},"partialResult":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"   320\t- On successful load of a supported legacy file, write back the canonical versioned format.\n   321\t- Do not persist adapter-only ephemeral state such as manual session overrides or other runtime-only session state.\n   322\t\n   323\t### Path ownership\n   324\t\n   325\t- The core must not hard-code a filesystem path.\n   326\t- The pi adapter should supply the default path for pi installs.\n   327\t- Non-pi consumers should be able to choose their own storage location while still using the same schema.\n   328\t\n   329\t## Error and retry semantics\n   330\t\n   331\t### Usage fetch\n   332\t\n   333\t- Classify retryable usage fetch errors as:\n   334\t  - abort-like errors\n   335\t  - HTTP 429\n   336\t  - HTTP 5xx\n   337\t  - obvious network failures\n   338\t- Retry with bounded backoff and then fall back to cached data if present.\n   339\t- If a fetch is aborted, do not emit a hard warning unless the adapter explicitly wants to.\n   340\t- If there is no cache and all retries fail, return `undefined` and let the adapter decide how to surface the warning.\n   341\t\n   342\t### Token refresh\n   343\t\n   344\t- Refresh only when the access token is close to expiry.\n   345\t- Concurrent refreshes for the same account must reuse one in-flight promise.\n   346\t- On refresh failure, surface a clear error and, if using `needsReauth`, mark the account accordingly.\n   347\t- Refresh failures must not corrupt the persisted account record.\n   348\t\n   349\t### Rotation during streaming\n   350\t\n   351\t- The adapter should rotate only when the failure is a quota/rate-limit failure **before any output** is forwarded.\n   352\t- Once the stream has emitted data, do not attempt a silent retry of the same request.\n   353\t- Failed attempts must be excluded from subsequent retries for that request.\n   354\t- Preserve abort semantics from the caller signal through to the provider stream.\n   355\t\n   356\t### Operational warnings\n   357\t\n   358\t- Non-fatal warnings should go through an injected logger/warning callback, not direct UI calls.\n   359\t- The core should never assume a UI is present.\n   360\t\n   361\t## Testing strategy\n   362\t\n   363\t### Core tests\n   364\t\n   365\tAdd unit tests that are independent of pi runtime:\n   366\t\n   367\t- quota error classification\n   368\t- usage parsing and reset conversion\n   369\t- untouched-usage detection\n   370\t- selection heuristics\n   371\t- exhausted-account exclusion\n   372\t- account refresh caching behavior\n   373\t- token refresh deduplication\n   374\t- quota cooldown marking\n   375\t- storage migration and salvage behavior\n   376\t\n   377\t### Adapter tests\n   378\t\n   379\tKeep or add tests for the pi boundary:\n   380\t\n   381\t- provider config mirrors `openai-codex` metadata\n   382\t- extension startup skips provider registration and warns when `openai-codex-responses` is unavailable\n   383\t- stream wrapper forwards the selected account header\n   384\t- manual account takes precedence over auto-selection\n   385\t- quota-before-output triggers rotation\n   386\t- quota-after-output does not retry silently\n   387\t- command wiring still exposes the documented commands\n   388\t- session hooks still refresh/activate accounts on startup/new sessions\n   389\t- root compatibility barrel still exposes the current exported names used by `index.test.ts`\n   390\t\n   391\t### Regression strategy\n   392\t\n   393\t- Split the current `index.test.ts` into focused tests by module boundary.\n   394\t- Preserve a small compatibility smoke suite at the root until the transition is complete.\n   395\t- Use mocks for storage, token refresh, usage fetch, and base provider to keep tests deterministic.\n   396\t- If adopting any source-implementation improvements such as `needsReauth` or refresh dedupe, add tests before wiring them into the adapter.\n   397\t\n   398\t## Phased rollout plan\n   399\t\n   400\t### Phase 1 â€” carve out pure helpers\n   401\t\n   402\t- Move quota classification, usage parsing, selection helpers, and related types into core modules.\n   403\t- Keep root exports as shims so nothing breaks.\n   404\t- Add focused unit tests for the new pure modules.\n   405\t\n   406\t### Phase 2 â€” extract core state manager\n   407\t\n   408\t- Move account persistence, refresh orchestration, token refresh, cooldown handling, and usage caching into `multicodex-core`.\n   409\t- Introduce storage and token-refresh injection points.\n   410\t- Add migration tests for old storage files.\n   411\t- Keep current external behavior unchanged.\n   412\t\n   413\t### Phase 3 â€” rewire the pi adapter\n   414\t\n   415\t- Replace direct monolith logic with core calls.\n   416\t- Move commands, provider registration, hooks, and stream wrapper behavior into adapter modules.\n   417\t- Preserve the documented command names and current user-visible output.\n   418\t- Remove remaining core dependencies on pi runtime types.\n   419\t\n   420\t### Phase 4 â€” non-pi validation\n   421\t\n   422\t- Add at least one non-pi validation path that exercises the core without `@mariozechner/pi-coding-agent` imports.\n   423\t- This validation may be a small test harness, CLI smoke script, or gateway spike.\n   424\t- Shipping a productized gateway/service is optional; proving the core is reusable outside pi is required.\n   425\t\n   426\t## Risks and open questions\n   427\t\n   428\t- **Storage path canonicalization:** the current repo and the reference implementation use different storage file names/locations. The migration layer must choose one canonical path and keep backward-compatible reads from the other.\n   429\t- **Selection heuristic divergence:** the reference implementation includes a lower-usage tie-breaker that is not part of the current repo behavior contract. Do not adopt it silently.\n   430\t- **Auth-failure tracking:** the reference uses `needsReauth`. Decide whether this becomes part of the shared core state model or stays adapter-specific.\n   431\t- **Manual override scope:** manual account selection should likely remain session-local and not be persisted; verify that no adapter expects persistence.\n   432\t- **Core HTTP dependency:** decide whether `UsageClient` owns the `fetch` implementation or whether the adapter injects it for broader portability.\n   433\t- **Gateway shape:** if a gateway follows, confirm whether it needs streaming event translation or only account/token selection.\n   434\t\n   435\t## Definition of done\n   436\t\n   437\t- The monolith has been split into a reusable core boundary and a pi-specific adapter boundary inside the existing package structure.\n   438\t- Core logic no longer imports pi runtime APIs.\n   439\t- Existing pi commands and provider behavior remain functionally equivalent to the current documented behavior in `README.md`, including `/multicodex-login`, `/multicodex-use`, and `/multicodex-status`.\n   440\t- The bounded usage retry policy remains equivalent to the current code (`2` retries with approximately `300ms` then `900ms` backoff) unless tests/docs are updated together.\n   441\t- The bounded stream-rotation policy remains equivalent to the current code (maximum `5` rotation retries) unless tests/docs are updated together.\n   442\t- Legacy storage from the current monolith loads successfully and migrates to the canonical versioned schema without data loss for valid accounts.\n   443\t- Retry/rotation, usage-cache behavior, and root compatibility exports are covered by regression tests.\n   444\t- The repo includes one non-pi validation path that exercises the core without pi runtime imports.\n   445\t- `README.md` includes minimal migration notes confirming the internal core/adapter split and that the existing pi install/command surface is unchanged.\n   446\t- `npm run lint`, `npm run tsgo`, and `npm run test` all pass.\n"}],"details":{}}}
{"type":"tool_execution_end","toolCallId":"call_bCAW8Oj1ytwWlsMIBKucn0tf|fc_09e1a19d9e220e560169de0ad88854819abd96cdcc2d83fcb6","toolName":"bash","result":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"   320\t- On successful load of a supported legacy file, write back the canonical versioned format.\n   321\t- Do not persist adapter-only ephemeral state such as manual session overrides or other runtime-only session state.\n   322\t\n   323\t### Path ownership\n   324\t\n   325\t- The core must not hard-code a filesystem path.\n   326\t- The pi adapter should supply the default path for pi installs.\n   327\t- Non-pi consumers should be able to choose their own storage location while still using the same schema.\n   328\t\n   329\t## Error and retry semantics\n   330\t\n   331\t### Usage fetch\n   332\t\n   333\t- Classify retryable usage fetch errors as:\n   334\t  - abort-like errors\n   335\t  - HTTP 429\n   336\t  - HTTP 5xx\n   337\t  - obvious network failures\n   338\t- Retry with bounded backoff and then fall back to cached data if present.\n   339\t- If a fetch is aborted, do not emit a hard warning unless the adapter explicitly wants to.\n   340\t- If there is no cache and all retries fail, return `undefined` and let the adapter decide how to surface the warning.\n   341\t\n   342\t### Token refresh\n   343\t\n   344\t- Refresh only when the access token is close to expiry.\n   345\t- Concurrent refreshes for the same account must reuse one in-flight promise.\n   346\t- On refresh failure, surface a clear error and, if using `needsReauth`, mark the account accordingly.\n   347\t- Refresh failures must not corrupt the persisted account record.\n   348\t\n   349\t### Rotation during streaming\n   350\t\n   351\t- The adapter should rotate only when the failure is a quota/rate-limit failure **before any output** is forwarded.\n   352\t- Once the stream has emitted data, do not attempt a silent retry of the same request.\n   353\t- Failed attempts must be excluded from subsequent retries for that request.\n   354\t- Preserve abort semantics from the caller signal through to the provider stream.\n   355\t\n   356\t### Operational warnings\n   357\t\n   358\t- Non-fatal warnings should go through an injected logger/warning callback, not direct UI calls.\n   359\t- The core should never assume a UI is present.\n   360\t\n   361\t## Testing strategy\n   362\t\n   363\t### Core tests\n   364\t\n   365\tAdd unit tests that are independent of pi runtime:\n   366\t\n   367\t- quota error classification\n   368\t- usage parsing and reset conversion\n   369\t- untouched-usage detection\n   370\t- selection heuristics\n   371\t- exhausted-account exclusion\n   372\t- account refresh caching behavior\n   373\t- token refresh deduplication\n   374\t- quota cooldown marking\n   375\t- storage migration and salvage behavior\n   376\t\n   377\t### Adapter tests\n   378\t\n   379\tKeep or add tests for the pi boundary:\n   380\t\n   381\t- provider config mirrors `openai-codex` metadata\n   382\t- extension startup skips provider registration and warns when `openai-codex-responses` is unavailable\n   383\t- stream wrapper forwards the selected account header\n   384\t- manual account takes precedence over auto-selection\n   385\t- quota-before-output triggers rotation\n   386\t- quota-after-output does not retry silently\n   387\t- command wiring still exposes the documented commands\n   388\t- session hooks still refresh/activate accounts on startup/new sessions\n   389\t- root compatibility barrel still exposes the current exported names used by `index.test.ts`\n   390\t\n   391\t### Regression strategy\n   392\t\n   393\t- Split the current `index.test.ts` into focused tests by module boundary.\n   394\t- Preserve a small compatibility smoke suite at the root until the transition is complete.\n   395\t- Use mocks for storage, token refresh, usage fetch, and base provider to keep tests deterministic.\n   396\t- If adopting any source-implementation improvements such as `needsReauth` or refresh dedupe, add tests before wiring them into the adapter.\n   397\t\n   398\t## Phased rollout plan\n   399\t\n   400\t### Phase 1 â€” carve out pure helpers\n   401\t\n   402\t- Move quota classification, usage parsing, selection helpers, and related types into core modules.\n   403\t- Keep root exports as shims so nothing breaks.\n   404\t- Add focused unit tests for the new pure modules.\n   405\t\n   406\t### Phase 2 â€” extract core state manager\n   407\t\n   408\t- Move account persistence, refresh orchestration, token refresh, cooldown handling, and usage caching into `multicodex-core`.\n   409\t- Introduce storage and token-refresh injection points.\n   410\t- Add migration tests for old storage files.\n   411\t- Keep current external behavior unchanged.\n   412\t\n   413\t### Phase 3 â€” rewire the pi adapter\n   414\t\n   415\t- Replace direct monolith logic with core calls.\n   416\t- Move commands, provider registration, hooks, and stream wrapper behavior into adapter modules.\n   417\t- Preserve the documented command names and current user-visible output.\n   418\t- Remove remaining core dependencies on pi runtime types.\n   419\t\n   420\t### Phase 4 â€” non-pi validation\n   421\t\n   422\t- Add at least one non-pi validation path that exercises the core without `@mariozechner/pi-coding-agent` imports.\n   423\t- This validation may be a small test harness, CLI smoke script, or gateway spike.\n   424\t- Shipping a productized gateway/service is optional; proving the core is reusable outside pi is required.\n   425\t\n   426\t## Risks and open questions\n   427\t\n   428\t- **Storage path canonicalization:** the current repo and the reference implementation use different storage file names/locations. The migration layer must choose one canonical path and keep backward-compatible reads from the other.\n   429\t- **Selection heuristic divergence:** the reference implementation includes a lower-usage tie-breaker that is not part of the current repo behavior contract. Do not adopt it silently.\n   430\t- **Auth-failure tracking:** the reference uses `needsReauth`. Decide whether this becomes part of the shared core state model or stays adapter-specific.\n   431\t- **Manual override scope:** manual account selection should likely remain session-local and not be persisted; verify that no adapter expects persistence.\n   432\t- **Core HTTP dependency:** decide whether `UsageClient` owns the `fetch` implementation or whether the adapter injects it for broader portability.\n   433\t- **Gateway shape:** if a gateway follows, confirm whether it needs streaming event translation or only account/token selection.\n   434\t\n   435\t## Definition of done\n   436\t\n   437\t- The monolith has been split into a reusable core boundary and a pi-specific adapter boundary inside the existing package structure.\n   438\t- Core logic no longer imports pi runtime APIs.\n   439\t- Existing pi commands and provider behavior remain functionally equivalent to the current documented behavior in `README.md`, including `/multicodex-login`, `/multicodex-use`, and `/multicodex-status`.\n   440\t- The bounded usage retry policy remains equivalent to the current code (`2` retries with approximately `300ms` then `900ms` backoff) unless tests/docs are updated together.\n   441\t- The bounded stream-rotation policy remains equivalent to the current code (maximum `5` rotation retries) unless tests/docs are updated together.\n   442\t- Legacy storage from the current monolith loads successfully and migrates to the canonical versioned schema without data loss for valid accounts.\n   443\t- Retry/rotation, usage-cache behavior, and root compatibility exports are covered by regression tests.\n   444\t- The repo includes one non-pi validation path that exercises the core without pi runtime imports.\n   445\t- `README.md` includes minimal migration notes confirming the internal core/adapter split and that the existing pi install/command surface is unchanged.\n   446\t- `npm run lint`, `npm run tsgo`, and `npm run test` all pass.\n"}]},"isError":false}
