{"type":"message_update","assistantMessageEvent":{"type":"toolcall_end","contentIndex":1,"toolCall":{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_y5idScs80v1CJoGgl0sD6CS1|fc_09e1a19d9e220e560169de0afcc1c8819ab1c7dbd2c5b6687b","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/home/linkdevk/repos/kg-multicodex/.agents/tasks/refactor-agnostic/progress.md","edits":[{"oldText":"## Review\n- What's correct\n  - The spec matches the current README/code on the documented command surface (`/multicodex-login`, `/multicodex-use`, `/multicodex-status`), the selection heuristic shape, the usage cache/retry constants, and the thin-adapter target.\n- Fixed: Issue and resolution\n  - Captured the main blocking mismatches for follow-up: context docs still mention `/multicodex-switch` and require a non-pi consumer, while the spec/code currently target `/multicodex-use` and treat the gateway spike as optional.\n- Note: Observations\n  - Token refresh deduplication, widened public interfaces, and reference-implementation storage migration are not all part of the current code contract, so the spec should mark them as explicit scope additions or narrow them.\n","newText":"## Review\n- What's correct\n  - `plan.md` follows the spec-linked phased rollout exactly: Stage 1 extracts pure helpers, Stage 2 extracts the reusable core manager/storage boundary, Stage 3 rewires the pi adapter and compatibility barrel, and Stage 4 adds non-pi validation plus the final regression sweep.\n  - The concrete module split mostly matches the spec extraction map: `core/{types,errors,retry,usage,selection,storage,usage-client,account-manager}.ts`, `adapter/pi/{oauth,browser,stream-utils,status,provider,stream-wrapper,commands,hooks,index}.ts`, and root `index.ts` as the compatibility shim.\n  - The plan preserves the main architecture intent that `multicodex-core` owns selection/cache/refresh/cooldown/storage behavior while the pi adapter owns commands, provider registration, browser/UI behavior, hooks, and stream/event shaping.\n- Fixed: Issue and resolution\n  - No plan files were edited in this review pass; instead, the remaining alignment issues were documented for follow-up before implementation starts.\n- Note: Observations\n  - The plan does not yet explicitly lock in several parity items the spec treats as required regression coverage: `excludeEmails` selection behavior, selected-account header injection, startup warn/skip when `openai-codex-responses` is unavailable, session hook behavior, and the maximum-5 stream rotation bound.\n  - Stage 2 currently treats token refresh deduplication as optional, but the specâ€™s error semantics/tests require concurrent per-account refreshes to share one in-flight promise, so the plan should either adopt that requirement explicitly or the spec must be narrowed.\n  - `adapter/pi/storage.ts` is a reasonable addition for path ownership even though it is not listed in the specâ€™s recommended file layout; if kept, the final implementation should ensure the core still owns only the abstract storage contract and never the pi path.\n"}]}},"partial":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Identifying specification inconsistencies**\n\nI've noticed that the plan states that token refresh deduplication is an optional enhancement, but the specification later treats it as a must-have and includes tests for it. That feels like a misalignmentâ€”definitely a great catch! Also, the stage 2 tests mention expired-token refresh but donâ€™t explicitly include refresh deduplication. Since the spec states itâ€™s required, there's a significant gap here. I should probably note that the spec is internally inconsistent, and I want to ensure the plan aligns with the explicit requirements.\n\n**Evaluating project specifications**\n\nI might want to suggest an update to the spec plan, mentioning the file layout to help reduce drift. Since I'm looking at the plan, rather than the spec, it might be better to just note that there's an accepted divergence. Criterion 4 requires that file moves and module boundaries align with the extraction map, and I think that's fine overall. The plan includes the adapter/pi/storage.ts, which satisfies path ownership, so no fix needed. Iâ€™ll also document the phase rollout approach.\n\n**Updating review section**\n\nIâ€™m considering updating the next step based on the user's request to just review. It seems like a good idea to focus solely on that Review section. Iâ€™ll edit the `progress.md` file to replace the existing text in the Review section with my current findings. Keeping it clear and relevant will be essential since thatâ€™s what the user is looking for! Letâ€™s make those changes!","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_09e1a19d9e220e560169de0add0058819a8c19044d9a4590be\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp3gr8ckzdQMhuMOj4l0AgiDxL9H0pCpjcaUq9_fyDfdtEOODRp2TPQKXjx7EWHcHUkI99MRECutPfMGPxDSb50XZruF_Qi_5epJ4Bx3NjacqoITi8myteTv_QTu7FrwfvhSqOoJZ9SCO94jjBXVZpXmRLBZRt7quefHwQfX9Y_oVIaUpXcRW8-SrNNlAu4_DPYKhBftuHnWbVrKG5wYtwi5-DSQoWd9cMmSBb0_iORY4_3P30rrIC6NVVfk8DS_GjhQyy9tF09x7QC-TPKc-Pvvs1scK5m678hgtU5wRD0ujIqjiUVp1IUMyQKkQb6korPeQl6w8EuxcKUVeBGxfXFaL8k65qpViDquqx-qGbk1a4JB4iJQ8zQkUQzHFPteRA-s9C9DSkmxU4VYvo8ibm1UiZQTQ_Erl87eq1LeYBftiJ_ZCFvk9NA29UZxVBOi9lWKySNLwDdJMgyecOVcPqR31s5f7elN95Li5kLKGtndwGkEr936Zaq3ZekLRVW2cB_V0vZIFFZxyrpeuvbQr83nS4U6NfyhMSrc_90wzkgzNc8TjHOd6ANxSJ73ZHj63PiRhEmjIh0EC4L2UQ0Q0pEw3jP5lOfbARjRNxmm8oOggPXvaF6eJpzDNPrHzOhEGPzA46UNXeLE61E9TT9vGJl0zL1bM-JhN53r3NOcp8Bfoo08MCK3e74A3Z5-8hs7npUu9mMr95w3pl6dNMQ_luUMbSdHYiZ6zNDsA0ibHM1h4Sx08gYHcEy68u1fUlGpvWHQr9yOCYDOI3wlDStckHxe8_aupvumwp688u7UQaBUxpokizN4LL5L9ZoqAJM-XcOKp2bUr9hYkAXTom01RWPjyaK6K7jeZmDrXbQ6aXOrjnLu2gzBXkyKhgA385ZjAZ3tg5FxW9ch_lxSU3ka8doMJJvJLFVIIi7qsqrTBu889URbDNh3gARL6J5u9Ew8NLiqqk4RIR1ifBnqT7o5n2-Sds46gxWqjFLjJL_hnI8oL9mzwLPu4nkDH327p0Q45wSxXif-n1-9jpAgvQHPA6kl7A334jleN1qt0mqQjVQ_t4fbA6uX5n-KvFSfncSS-0UXnzIedUabT1kH8_cIvNBoqodp5ZtSJI2sQBwfhXgrfh00TdueRqcRB3xpYol6qGn8xUwJmCdfvqqgaJ_LDm5qFZ