s/refactor-agnostic/progress.md","edits":[{"oldText":"## Review\n- What's correct\n  - The spec matches the current README/code on the documented command surface (`/multicodex-login`, `/multicodex-use`, `/multicodex-status`), the selection heuristic shape, the usage cache/retry constants, and the thin-adapter target.\n- Fixed: Issue and resolution\n  - Captured the main blocking mismatches for follow-up: context docs still mention `/multicodex-switch` and require a non-pi consumer, while the spec/code currently target `/multicodex-use` and treat the gateway spike as optional.\n- Note: Observations\n  - Token refresh deduplication, widened public interfaces, and reference-implementation storage migration are not all part of the current code contract, so the spec should mark them as explicit scope additions or narrow them.\n","newText":"## Review\n- What's correct\n  - `plan.md` follows the spec-linked phased rollout exactly: Stage 1 extracts pure helpers, Stage 2 extracts the reusable core manager/storage boundary, Stage 3 rewires the pi adapter and compatibility barrel, and Stage 4 adds non-pi validation plus the final regression sweep.\n  - The concrete module split mostly matches the spec extraction map: `core/{types,errors,retry,usage,selection,storage,usage-client,account-manager}.ts`, `adapter/pi/{oauth,browser,stream-utils,status,provider,stream-wrapper,commands,hooks,index}.ts`, and root `index.ts` as the compatibility shim.\n  - The plan preserves the main architecture intent that `multicodex-core` owns selection/cache/refresh/cooldown/storage behavior while the pi adapter owns commands, provider registration, browser/UI behavior, hooks, and stream/event shaping.\n- Fixed: Issue and resolution\n  - No plan files were edited in this review pass; instead, the remaining alignment issues were documented for follow-up before implementation starts.\n- Note: Observations\n  - The plan does not yet explicitly lock in several parity items the spec treats as required regression coverage: `excludeEmails` selection behavior, selected-account header injection, startup warn/skip when `openai-codex-responses` is unavailable, session hook behavior, and the maximum-5 stream rotation bound.\n  - Stage 2 currently treats token refresh deduplication as optional, but the specâ€™s error semantics/tests require concurrent per-account refreshes to share one in-flight promise, so the plan should either adopt that requirement explicitly or the spec must be narrowed.\n  - `adapter/pi/storage.ts` is a reasonable addition for path ownership even though it is not listed in the specâ€™s recommended file layout; if kept, the final implementation should ensure the core still owns only the abstract storage contract and never the pi path.\n"}]},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"/home/linkdevk/repos/kg-multicodex/.agents/tasks/refactor-agnostic/progress.md\",\"edits\":[{\"oldText\":\"## Review\\n- What's correct\\n  - The spec matches the current README/code on the documented command surface (`/multicodex-login`, `/multicodex-use`, `/multicodex-status`), the selection heuristic shape, the usage cache/retry constants, and the thin-adapter target.\\n- Fixed: Issue and resolution\\n  - Captured the main blocking mismatches for follow-up: context docs still mention `/multicodex-switch` and require a non-pi consumer, while the spec/code currently target `/multicodex-use` and treat the gateway spike as optional.\\n- Note: Observations\\n  - Token refresh deduplication, widened public interfaces, and reference-implementation storage migration are not all part of the current code contract, so the spec should mark them as explicit scope additions or narrow them.\\n\",\"newText\":\"## Review\\n- What's correct\\n  - `plan.md` follows the spec-linked phased rollout exactly: Stage 1 extracts pure helpers, Stage 2 extracts the reusable core manager/storage boundary, Stage 3 rewires the pi adapter and compatibility barrel, and Stage 4 adds non-pi validation plus the final regression sweep.\\n  - The concrete module split mostly matches the spec extraction map: `core/{types,errors,retry,usage,selection,storage,usage-client,account-manager}.ts`, `adapter/pi/{oauth,browser,stream-utils,status,provider,stream-wrapper,commands,hooks,index}.ts`, and root `index.ts` as the compatibility shim.\\n  - The plan preserves the main architecture intent that `multicodex-core` owns selection/cache/refresh/cooldown/storage behavior while the pi adapter owns commands, provider registration, browser/UI behavior, hooks, and stream/event shaping.\\n- Fixed: Issue and resolution\\n  - No plan files were edited in this review pass; instead, the remaining alignment issues were documented for follow-up before implementation starts.\\n- Note: Observations\\n  - The plan does not yet explicitly lock in several parity items the spec treats as required regression coverage: `excludeEmails` selection behavior, selected-account header injection, startup warn/skip when `openai-codex-responses` is unavailable, session hook behavior, and the maximum-5 stream rotation bound.\\n  - Stage 2 currently treats token refresh deduplication as optional, but the specâ€™s error semantics/tests require concurrent per-account refreshes to share one in-flight promise, so the plan should either adopt that requirement explicitly or the spec must be narrowed.\\n  - `adapter/pi/storage.ts` is a reasonable addition for path ownership even though it is not listed in the specâ€™s recommended file layout; if kept, the final implementation should ensure the core still owns only the abstract storage contract and never the pi path.\\n\"}]}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":1966,"output":1899,"cacheRead":52096,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":55961,"cost":{"input":0.004915,"output":0.028485,"cacheRead":0.013023999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.046424}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776159448805,"responseId":"resp_09e1a19d9e220e56