{"type":"message_update","assistantMessageEvent":{"type":"text_end","contentIndex":1,"content":"I reviewed the plan against the spec. Overall: **mostly aligned, but not fully spec-complete yet**.\n\n## What's correct\n\n- **Behavior-preserving intent is clear.**  \n  `plan.md` keeps the stated goal of extracting a reusable core without changing the documented pi surface.  \n  - Plan: `.agents/tasks/refactor-agnostic/plan.md:8`\n  - Spec: `.agents/tasks/refactor-agnostic/spec.md:5-8`\n\n- **The phased rollout matches the spec exactly.**  \n  Stages 1â€“4 line up with the required sequence:\n  1. pure helpers\n  2. core state manager\n  3. pi adapter rewiring\n  4. non-pi validation  \n  - Plan: `.agents/tasks/refactor-agnostic/plan.md:10-35`\n  - Spec: `.agents/tasks/refactor-agnostic/spec.md:398-424`\n\n- **The target architecture is mostly respected.**\n  - Stage 1/2 move domain logic, storage, refresh, selection, usage, and cooldown into `core/*`.\n  - Stage 3 moves commands, provider wiring, browser/OAuth, hooks, stream/event shaping into `adapter/pi/*`.  \n  This is consistent with:\n  - `multicodex-core` owning domain/state behavior\n  - `multicodex-pi-adapter` owning pi integration  \n  - Plan: stage 1â€“3\n  - Spec: `.agents/tasks/refactor-agnostic/spec.md:130-184`\n\n- **The module split is largely correct per the extraction map.**\n  The plan covers nearly all mapped targets:\n  - `core/{types,errors,retry,usage,selection,storage,usage-client,account-manager}.ts`\n  - `adapter/pi/{oauth,browser,stream-utils,status,provider,stream-wrapper,commands,hooks,index}.ts`\n  - root `index.ts` as compatibility barrel  \n  - Spec extraction map: `.agents/tasks/refactor-agnostic/spec.md:194-232`\n\n- **Definition-of-done coverage is mostly present.**\n  The plan addresses:\n  - pi-free core\n  - legacy storage migration\n  - README note preservation\n  - non-pi validation path\n  - final `lint/tsgo/test` checks  \n  - Plan: stage 2, 3, 4\n  - Spec DoD: `.agents/tasks/refactor-agnostic/spec.md:435-446`\n\n## What needs to be fixed\n\n### 1) Token refresh deduplication is misaligned\nThis is the biggest mismatch.\n\nThe plan currently treats refresh dedupe as optional:\n- `.agents/tasks/refactor-agnostic/plan.md:41`\n- Stage 2 also does **not** explicitly require or test it:\n  - `.agents/tasks/refactor-agnostic/stages/extract-core-state-manager-and-storage.md:10-25`\n\nBut the spec later makes it a requirement:\n- concurrent refreshes for the same account must share one in-flight promise  \n  - `.agents/tasks/refactor-agnostic/spec.md:344-347`\n- core tests should cover token refresh deduplication  \n  - `.agents/tasks/refactor-agnostic/spec.md:365-375`\n\n**Fix:** Stage 2 should explicitly require per-account refresh dedupe and add dedicated tests, or the spec must be narrowed. As written, the plan is not fully aligned.\n\n---\n\n### 2) Several required parity behaviors are not explicitly covered in the planâ€™s regression criteria\nThe plan mentions â€śfull behavior parity,â€ť but the explicit test list is incomplete.\n\nMissing or under-specified:\n- `excludeEmails` must be honored during retries  \n  - Spec: `.agents/tasks/refactor-agnostic/spec.md:84-92`\n- selected account header injection  \n  - Spec: `.agents/tasks/refactor-agnostic/spec.md:116-121`\n- warn/skip when `openai-codex-responses` is unavailable  \n  - Spec: `.agents/tasks/refactor-agnostic/spec.md:116-121`, `377-389`\n- session hook behavior on startup/new session  \n  - Spec: `.agents/tasks/refactor-agnostic/spec.md:377-389`\n- command wiring exposure\n  - Spec: `.agents/tasks/refactor-agnostic/spec.md:377-389`\n- root compatibility export smoke\n  - Spec: `.agents/tasks/refactor-agnostic/spec.md:238-255`, `377-389`\n\nThe current plan only explicitly calls out a subset:\n- Stage 3 tests: provider mirroring, manual selection, stream rotation, event translation  \n  - `.agents/tasks/refactor-agnostic/stages/rewire-pi-adapter-and-compatibility-barrel.md:22-29`\n- Stage 4 tests: manual precedence, usage parsing, untouched detection, cached refresh, token threshold, quota-before-output, quota-after-output  \n  - `.agents/tasks/refactor-agnostic/stages/add-non-pi-validation-and-parity-regression-coverage.md:13-23`\n\n**Fix:** Expand Stage 3/4 explicit test bullets and success criteria to name these missing behaviors.\n\n---\n\n### 3) The stream rotation bound is not pinned strongly enough\nThe spec requires equivalence to the current max rotation bound:\n- max **5** rotation retries  \n  - `.agents/tasks/refactor-agnostic/spec.md:441-443`\n\nThe plan only says:\n- â€śbounded retry loopâ€ť  \n  - `.agents/tasks/refactor-agnostic/stages/rewire-pi-adapter-and-compatibility-barrel.md:17`\n\nThat is too loose for a parity-sensitive refactor.\n\n**Fix:** State the numeric bound explicitly in Stage 3 and add regression coverage for it in Stage 4.\n\n---\n\n### 4) Retry-policy ownership is a little ambiguous\nStage 2 says:\n- move `fetchCodexUsage` into `core/usage-client.ts` while preserving timeout and retry semantics  \n  - `.agents/tasks/refactor-agnostic/stages/extract-core-state-manager-and-storage.md:12`\n\nBut the specâ€™s architecture suggests:\n- HTTP client is injectable\n- cache/refresh policy belongs to the core manager  \n  - `.agents/tasks/refactor-agnostic/spec.md:154-162`, `331-340`\n\nThis could lead to retry/backoff policy being split awkwardly between `usage-client` and `account-manager`.\n\n**Fix:** Clarify whether bounded retry/backoff + cached fallback live in:\n- `account-manager` orchestration, with `usage-client` as a single-attempt fetcher, or\n- `usage-client`, with a clearly defined manager contract.\n\nRight now itâ€™s not wrong, but it is underspecified.\n\n## Concrete file/module boundary assessment\n\n**Correct overall.**  \nThe planâ€™s file moves mostly match the specâ€™s extraction map.\n\nOne minor note:\n- `adapter/pi/storage.ts` is **not listed** in the specâ€™s recommended file layout, but it is consistent with the specâ€™s path-ownership rule that the pi adapter should supply the default filesystem path while core stays path-agnostic. So Iâ€™d call this **acceptable**, not a problem.\n  - Plan: `.agents/tasks/refactor-agnostic/stages/rewire-pi-adapter-and-compatibility-barrel.md:11`\n  - Spec path ownership: `.agents/tasks/refactor-agnostic/spec.md:323-327`\n\n## Definition of done assessment\n\n**Partially addressed; not fully locked down yet.**\n\nCovered:\n- core/adapter split\n- pi-free core\n- legacy storage migration\n- non-pi validation\n- README note\n- final checks\n\nNot explicitly locked down enough:\n- max-5 rotation equivalence\n- refresh dedupe requirement\n- complete regression coverage for adapter parity cases\n\n## Bottom line\n\n**Verdict: good structure, but not approval-ready yet.**\n\n### Blocking issues\n1. Refresh dedupe requirement is not aligned with the spec.\n2. Stage 3/4 regression coverage does not explicitly enumerate several required parity behaviors.\n3. Max-5 rotation bound needs to be explicit.\n\nI also updated:\n- `.agents/tasks/refactor-agnostic/progress.md`\n\nIf you want, I can now patch `plan.md` and the stage docs to close these gaps.","partial":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_09e1a19d9e220e560169de0b1ab578819ab89a7f6cd198d553\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp3gskYGZtSg7ozLl_ZHETLHN-11C8hGTwAIhB9htDXwLYzt_MVPtOhi033Ovwuz1mK5SMYG-bStO3iaGXNhRT9w7UO9SIkj4bqp0ByuXKy51m6aEQnmTEkDiacgcMccYx_kt9HqqbEXU8mwiuYJTRyjWLp9lWEd2DZQ-EeIulg_yoMCQlUdtQe581zPdO3kyjF8ApzmU4wevhEoaFHLMXk9BlR6DN7mhdMTbhgniggYGRHmX6p9Jf56ol_NzdYhOjkpQgq7rv6uO6O-yE13zVb4uL_pbKe4CMLKElmiRVTzQFuF5q8SB9lkd7bM5s5X-SU7l36irateQcsdJpUBG5ovV6rOBS43dKGcjFwJXAkM_XjByGsPpJyCANjmnKhdiPmQS-C9YVlAIyB0hGw6Eu7TEERcya_GGD14IyREKnS7VZsFBVTvwYqvSNKPf3AhizmG2AZGhCy1psaxZhvgTPuceyqjLGUZjC-NK14MG0nbHl5f0ec6Eh5raZR4Wrsr1OQ4Y2ct3tiasAKqI1R8iIpcxxrOZR-_DkzgnQvQF4S2DKgZt7pMasHwaEBWuoAocx3