ol to read multiple files at once? That seems efficient! Iâ€™ll need to check that the files are complete and under 2000 lines to ensure they're manageable. Inspecting the task directory and skill documentation could be my next step, maybe also in parallel.\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_EF1h9eQXCp9D5ilBDA27gkdI|fc_09e1a19d9e220e560169de0a0886dc819abee534d09c8a9763","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/linkdevk/repos/pi-subagents-v2/skills/reviewer/SKILL.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"/home/linkdevk/repos/pi-subagents-v2/skills/reviewer/SKILL.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_8EtEg4WqZrfGSwtJ92gzZc57|fc_09e1a19d9e220e560169de0a0886f0819a9fb8f6ed8c7a5f0b","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/linkdevk/repos/pi-subagents-v2/skills/reviewer/references/plan-review.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"/home/linkdevk/repos/pi-subagents-v2/skills/reviewer/references/plan-review.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_7G47MltdI2AwcqueratS4E8m|fc_09e1a19d9e220e560169de0a0886fc819a884c553d8ca557d5","name":"ls","arguments":{"path":"/home/linkdevk/repos/kg-multicodex/.agents/tasks/refactor-agnostic"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"/home/linkdevk/repos/kg-multicodex/.agents/tasks/refactor-agnostic\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":180,"output":169,"cacheRead":17792,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18141,"cost":{"input":0.00045000000000000004,"output":0.002535,"cacheRead":0.004448,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0074329999999999995}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776159235936,"responseId":"resp_09e1a19d9e220e560169de0a04ab68819a875355eb7862f6b2"},{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_EF1h9eQXCp9D5ilBDA27gkdI|fc_09e1a19d9e220e560169de0a0886dc819abee534d09c8a9763","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: reviewer\ndescription: Use when a user asks to review a spec or plan.\n---\n\nYou are a Senior Engineer, specialized in reviewing specs, plans, and implementations.\nYou are responsible for ensuring the success of the project.\nIf it fails, it will be YOUR FAULT. You MUST leave no stone unturned.\n\nNEVER GIVE UP! NEVER SURRENDER!\n\n## Concept Definitions\n- **Spec**: Distilled thoughts that define the **what** and **how** at a conceptual level. They are the initial formulation before any structured planning begins.\n- **Plan**: Structured implementation plan utilizing progressive disclosure. `plan.md` is the main document that contains the plan structure and state. Each stage has its own instructions file.\n- **Implementation**: Concrete code, tests, docs, and supporting artifacts that realize the plan.\n\n## Review Type Specific Instructions\nThere are three types of reviews: `spec`, `plan`, and `implementation`. Each type has ADDITIONAL instructions.\n\nIf its unclear which type of review is needed, use the following:\n- Has `spec.md` + no `plan.md` â†’ **Spec Review**\n- Has `plan.md` and no code/implementation target â†’ **Plan Review**\n- Has code changes, implementation artifacts, or explicit implementation target â†’ **Implementation Review**\n\n| Document Type | Reference File |\n| ------------- | -------------- |\n| Spec Review   | [references/spec-review.md](references/spec-review.md) |\n| Plan Review   | [references/plan-review.md](references/plan-review.md) |\n| Implementation Review | [references/implementation-review.md](references/implementation-review.md) |\n\n## Key Rules\nThese apply to all reviews.\n\n### Easy Issues Auto-fix (apply immediately)\n- **Deviations**: Implementation details/plan deviates from the initial intent or spec\n- **Bloat**: Tool explanations, verbose procedures, discoverable context, tool tutorials, conditional explanations\n- **Verbose language**: Replace procedures with outcomes, multi-step -> single action\n- **Dependency bloat**: Remove redundant/unused dependencies, or stages not referenced in instructions\n---\n**Auto-fix Examples**:\n- Remove: \"npm install\", \"run command\", \"I will now...\", tool tutorials\n- Simplify: \"Click the button and wait\" -> \"Button clicked\", \"Run 'ls' to see files\" -> (Delete)\n- Prefer: Use existing tools (Read/Edit/Grep) over generic bash commands when possible\n\n### Other Issues (use question tool)\n- **Gaps**: Missing prerequisites, incomplete success criteria, undocumented assumptions\n- **Inconsistencies**: Conflicting instructions, mismatched dependencies, naming drift\n- **Bad testing**: Brittle, flaky, redundant, or missing test coverage for critical paths\n- **Assumptions**: Hardcoded values without context, implicit state\n\n### Optimizations (suggest): \n- Parallelizable steps, prefer Read/Edit/Grep over bash\n\n### Test Review Rule\nFor both **plan reviews** and **implementation reviews**, when reviewing tests, test strategy, coverage quality, brittleness, or validation design, use the `quality-engineer` skill.\n\n## Output Format\n- \"Fixed: (Brief changelist of auto-fixes)\"\n- For medium+ issues: Use `question` tool to ask how to proceed\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776159240508},{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_8EtEg4WqZrfGSwtJ92gzZc57|fc_09e1a19d9e220e560169de0a0886f0819a9fb8f6ed8c7a5f0b","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Plan Review\n\nReview implementation plans for quality, completeness, and feasibility. Plans MUST target AI execution and follow progressive disclosure.\n\n## Target Paths\n- `.agents/tasks/<id>/plan.md`\n- `.agents/tasks/<id>/stages/*.md`\n\n## Plan-Specific Rules\n\n### Look For\n- **Deviations**: Plan deviates from the initial `spec`. Confirm plan is aligned with `plan.md` frontmatter `spec` property.\n- **Bloat**: Remove tool explanations, verbose procedures (\"I will now...\"), and discoverable context.\n- **Gaps**: Missing prerequisites, incomplete success criteria, or undocumented assumptions.\n- **Inconsistencies**: Conflicting instructions between stages, mismatched dependencies, or naming drift.\n- **Assumptions**: Hardcoded values without context, implicit state, or missing environment variables.\n- **Bad Testing**: Tests SHOULD be efficient. NO brittle or flaky tests. Tests SHOULD NOT be redundant.\n- **Optimizations**: Parallelizable steps, redundant I/O, missing tool preferences.\n- **Dependency Bloat**: \"Depends On\" lists stages not referenced or tested in instructions.\n\n### Test Review\nWhen reviewing planned tests, test strategy, coverage quality, brittleness, or validation design, use the `quality-engineer` skill.\n\n### Auto-fix Guidelines\n- **Remove**: \"npm install\", \"run command\", tool tutorials, conditional explanations.\n- **Simplify**: Procedures -> outcomes, multi-step -> single action.\n- **Prefer**: Existing tools (Read/Edit/Grep) over generic bash commands.\n- **Cleanup**: Remove stages not referenced or tested in stage instructions.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776159240508},{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_7G47MltdI2AwcqueratS4E8m|fc_09e1a19d9e220e560169de0a0886fc819a884c553d8ca557d5","toolName":"ls","content":[{"type":"text","text":"context/\ncontext.md\nplan.md\nprogress.md\nspec.md\nstages/"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776159240509},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Searching for skills**\n\nI'm trying to figure out if I need a quality-engineer skill for reviewing tests, but the available skills list only shows QA. The instruction clearly says to use the quality-engineer skill, which is a bit confusing. I wonder if it's a skill that exists but isnâ€™t listed properly. So, the next step is to search for skills and see if I can find this quality-engineer skill or more information about it. Let's go ahead and do that!","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_09e1a19d9e220e560169de0a0bda18819aa9325786efc597cc\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp3goOeapwF4UiPcWYotA_Fw5MVZNwp7c3iEHZbfCO8C5_BHKHVZwtkzajKP9xYGki1Z-fh1G6BLatZZsEcwPydpfFXrc7WjEPCsghyVnS3INOcqO7XOZrnlN7QZbjOq-nyw-mI1qpU_6_t_ZE7g_U92amyN3uBZKkj2WTSOyWIap_RnOU0UeW8tZ-wH