/refactor-agnostic/stages/extract-pure-helpers-and-shared-types.md && printf '\\\\n--- stage2 ---\\\\n' && nl -ba .agents/tasks/refactor-agnostic/stages/extract-core-state-manager-and-storage.md && printf '\\\\n--- stage3 ---\\\\n' && nl -ba .agents/tasks/refactor-agnostic/stages/rewire-pi-adapter-and-compatibility-barrel.md && printf '\\\\n--- stage4 ---\\\\n' && nl -ba .agents/tasks/refactor-agnostic/stages/add-non-pi-validation-and-parity-regression-coverage.md\",\"timeout\":10}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":1033,"output":430,"cacheRead":42880,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":44343,"cost":{"input":0.0025825,"output":0.00645,"cacheRead":0.01072,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0197525}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776159429233,"responseId":"resp_09e1a19d9e220e560169de0ac612a8819a9dd966a27ae87dd8"},{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_0sfaZgtJw5VNcEU8ZUDKguY2|fc_09e1a19d9e220e560169de0ad03788819abdf79d888a3ab5cd","toolName":"bash","content":[{"type":"text","text":"     1\t---\n     2\tid: refactor-agnostic\n     3\tspec: .agents/tasks/refactor-agnostic/spec.md\n     4\tstatus: ready\n     5\tupdated: 2026-04-14T00:00:00Z\n     6\t---\n     7\t\n     8\tExtract a platform-agnostic `multicodex-core` from the monolith, then rewire the pi adapter around it without changing the documented user-facing surface.\n     9\t\n    10\t## Stages\n    11\t- [ ] Stage 1:\n    12\t  - Title: Extract pure helpers and shared types\n    13\t  - Instructions: [extract-pure-helpers-and-shared-types.md](./stages/extract-pure-helpers-and-shared-types.md)\n    14\t  - Depends On: none\n    15\t\n    16\t- [ ] Stage 2:\n    17\t  - Title: Extract core state manager and storage\n    18\t  - Instructions: [extract-core-state-manager-and-storage.md](./stages/extract-core-state-manager-and-storage.md)\n    19\t  - Depends On: 1\n    20\t\n    21\t- [ ] Stage 3:\n    22\t  - Title: Rewire pi adapter and compatibility barrel\n    23\t  - Instructions: [rewire-pi-adapter-and-compatibility-barrel.md](./stages/rewire-pi-adapter-and-compatibility-barrel.md)\n    24\t  - Depends On: 2\n    25\t\n    26\t- [ ] Stage 4:\n    27\t  - Title: Add non-pi validation and parity regression coverage\n    28\t  - Instructions: [add-non-pi-validation-and-parity-regression-coverage.md](./stages/add-non-pi-validation-and-parity-regression-coverage.md)\n    29\t  - Depends On: 3\n    30\t\n    31\t## Dependency rationale\n    32\t- Stage 1 must land first because the selection, usage, and retry helpers are the pure seams that every later core module imports.\n    33\t- Stage 2 depends on Stage 1 because the state manager should be assembled on top of the extracted helpers and shared types, not by re-implementing them.\n    34\t- Stage 3 depends on Stage 2 because the pi adapter should become a thin consumer of the new core manager, storage adapter, and usage/token collaborators.\n    35\t- Stage 4 depends on Stage 3 because the final parity sweep should validate both the non-pi core reuse path and the adapter/root compatibility surface after the rewiring is complete.\n    36\t\n    37\t## Risks and edge cases\n    38\t- Storage migration must preserve the current legacy `~/.pi/agent/multicodex.json` shape while still writing a canonical versioned schema once the core loads it.\n    39\t- The reference implementationâ€™s lower-usage tie-breaker must not leak into the current selection policy unless tests/docs explicitly opt into it.\n    40\t- Manual account selection should stay session-local; do not persist adapter-only session overrides into storage.\n    41\t- Token refresh deduplication is an optional enhancement, not a required parity behavior, so it should not block the core extraction.\n    42\t- Adapter-specific browser launch failures must remain warnings, not hard crashes, in environments without an openable browser.\n\n--- stage1 ---\n     1\t---\n     2\tplan_id: refactor-agnostic\n     3\ttitle: extract pure helpers and shared types\n     4\tstatus: idle\n     5\tupdated: 2026-04-14T00:00:00Z\n     6\t---\n     7\t\n     8\tExtract the quota, usage, retry, and account-selection helpers into platform-agnostic modules with no pi runtime imports.\n     9\t\n    10\t## Steps\n    11\t- [ ] Create `core/types.ts` and move the shared data model there: `Account`, `StorageData`, and the canonical persisted account fields used by selection and persistence.\n    12\t- [ ] Create `core/errors.ts` and move `isQuotaErrorMessage`, `getErrorMessage`, `isAbortLikeError`, `getUsageHttpStatus`, and `isRetryableUsageError` into it.\n    13\t- [ ] Create `core/retry.ts` and move `sleepWithSignal` into it unchanged in behavior.\n    14\t- [ ] Create `core/usage.ts` and move `CodexUsageSnapshot`, `normalizeUsedPercent`, `normalizeResetAt`, `parseUsageWindow`, `parseCodexUsageResponse`, `isUsageUntouched`, `getNextResetAt`, and `getWeeklyResetAt` into it.\n    15\t- [ ] Create `core/selection.ts` and move `isAccountAvailable`, `pickRandomAccount`, `pickEarliestWeeklyResetAccount`, and `pickBestAccount` into it.\n    16\t- [ ] Create `core/index.ts` as a barrel that re-exports the current root-stable helper surface from the new core modules.\n    17\t- [ ] Keep `formatResetAt` out of core; it belongs in the pi adapter because it is presentation logic, not domain logic.\n    18\t- [ ] Split the current helper assertions out of `index.test.ts` into focused core tests that import only `core/*` modules.\n    19\t- [ ] Update the root `index.ts` to re-export the moved helper names through the new barrel without changing behavior.\n    20\t\n    21\t## Success Criteria\n    22\t- [ ] `core/*` modules can be imported without `@mariozechner/pi-ai` or `@mariozechner/pi-coding-agent`.\n    23\t- [ ] Unit coverage exists for quota classification, usage parsing/reset conversion, untouched-usage detection, and selection heuristics.\n    24\t- [ ] The root compatibility surface still exports `isQuotaErrorMessage`, `parseCodexUsageResponse`, `isUsageUntouched`, `getNextResetAt`, `getWeeklyResetAt`, and `pickBestAccount`.\n    25\t- [ ] No observable behavior changes for selection, parsing, or retry classification.\n\n--- stage2 ---\n     1\t---\n     2\tplan_id: refactor-agnostic\n     3\ttitle: extract core state manager and storage\n     4\tstatus: idle\n     5\tupdated: 2026-04-14T00:00:00Z\n     6\t---\n     7\t\n     8\tMove persistence, usage refresh, token refresh, cooldown bookkeeping, and account activation into `multicodex-core` behind injected collaborators.\n     9\t\n    10\t## Steps\n    11\t- [ ] Create `core/storage.ts` and define the platform-agnostic persistence contract: load/save adapter, canonical storage schema, and migration helpers for the legacy unversioned `{ accounts, activeEmail? }` file.\n    12\t- [ ] Create `core/usage-client.ts` and move `fetchCodexUsage` into an injectable client that accepts the access token, optional account id, and abort signal while preserving timeout and retry semantics.\n    13\t- [ ] Create `core/account-manager.ts` and move the stateful account manager behavior there: load/save, active/manual resolution, usage cache, usage refresh, selection activation, token validity, token refresh, and quota exhaustion handling.\n    14\t- [ ] Keep the manager API compatible with the current adapter needs: `getAccounts`, `getAccount`, `getActiveAccount`, `getManualAccount`, `hasManualAccount`, `getAvailableManualAccount`, `setActiveAccount`, `setManualAccount`, `clearManualAccount`, `addOrUpdateAccount`, `getCachedUsage`, `refreshUsageForAccount`, `refreshUsageForAllAccounts`, `refreshUsageIfStale`, `activateBestAccount`, `ensureValidToken`, and `handleQuotaExceeded`.\n    15\t- [ ] Inject the storage adapter, token refresher, usage client, clock, random source, and warning callback instead of hard-coding filesystem or pi APIs inside the manager.\n    16\t- [ ] Preserve the current usage cache TTL, retry policy, token freshness threshold, and quota cooldown fallback exactly unless tests/docs explicitly change them.\n    17\t- [ ] Add migration tests that load the current legacy storage file, normalize it to the canonical schema, and verify the written-back result is idempotent.\n    18\t- [ ] Add deterministic tests for cache hits, bounded retry/backoff, abort-like failures returning cached data, expired-token refresh, and quota cooldown marking.\n    19\t- [ ] Keep manual account selection session-local; do not persist manual overrides as part of storage migration.\n    20\t\n    21\t## Success Criteria\n    22\t- [ ] The core manager no longer imports node filesystem modules or pi runtime APIs directly.\n    23\t- [ ] Legacy storage loads successfully and saves back in the canonical versioned shape without losing valid account records.\n    24\t- [ ] The cache TTL, retry backoff, token refresh threshold, and cooldown behavior all match the current behavior contract.\n    25\t- [ ] The new core tests cover migration, refresh, cache, and cooldown behavior with injected fakes.\n\n--- stage3 ---\n     1\t---\n     2\tplan_id: refactor-agnostic\n     3\ttitle: rewire pi adapter and compatibility barrel\n     4\tstatus: idle\n     5\tupdated: 2026-04-14T00:00:00Z\n     6\t---\n     7\t\n     8\tMove pi-specific wiring out of the monolith so the adapter becomes a thin integration layer over the new core modules.\n     9\t\n    10\t## Steps\n    11\t- [ ] Create `adapter/pi/storage.ts` to own the default `~/.pi/agent/multicodex.json` path and implement the core storage interface using `node:fs`, `node:path`, and `node:os`.\n    12\t- [ ] Create `adapter/pi/oauth.ts` and move `resolveCodexOAuthFns`, `loginOpenAICodexCompat`, and `refreshOpenAICodexTokenCompat` there.\n    13\t- [ ] Create `adapter/pi/browser.ts` and move `openLoginInBrowser` there, keeping browser-open failures as warnings.\n    14\t- [ ] Create `adapter/pi/stream-utils.ts` and move `createErrorAssistantMessage`, `withProvider`, `createLinkedAbortController`, and `createTimeoutController` there.\n    15\t- [ ] Create `adapter/pi/status.ts` and move `formatResetAt` there.\n    16\t- [ ] Create `adapter/pi/provider.ts` and move `getOpenAICodexMirror` plus `buildMulticodexProviderConfig` there.\n    17\t- [ ] Create `adapter/pi/stream-wrapper.ts` and move `createStreamWrapper` there, preserving header injection, provider-id rewriting, quota-before-output rotation, and the bounded retry loop.\n    18\t- [ ] Create `adapter/pi/commands.ts` and move the `/multicodex-login`, `/multicodex-use`, and `/multicodex-status` handlers there without changing the user-visible strings or menu flow.\n    19\t- [ ] Create `adapter/pi/hooks.ts` and move the `session_start` and `session_switch` orchestration there.\n    20\t- [ ] Create `adapter/pi/index.ts` as the default extension entrypoint that wires the core manager, pi storage adapter, provider registration, commands, hooks, and warning routing together.\n    21\t- [ ] Update the root `index.ts` to act as a compatibility barrel and default-export shim that preserves the existing public names, including `Account`, `AccountManager`, `CodexUsageSnapshot`, `ProviderModelDef`, `buildMulticodexProviderConfig`, `createStreamWrapper`, `getNextResetAt`, `getOpenAICodexMirror`, `getWeeklyResetAt`, `isQuotaErrorMessage`, `isUsageUntouched`, `parseCodexUsageResponse`, `pickBestAccount`, and the default pi extension function.\n    22\t- [ ] Keep provider registration defensive: if `openai-codex-responses` is unavailable, warn and skip registration rather than crashing startup.\n    23\t- [ ] Move the adapter-focused assertions out of `index.test.ts` into dedicated pi-adapter tests for provider mirroring, manual selection, stream rotation, and event translation.\n    24\t\n    25\t## Success Criteria\n    26\t- [ ] The pi adapter owns all pi-specific API usage and the core tree remains pi-free.\n    27\t- [ ] The documented command surface and current output strings remain unchanged.\n    28\t- [ ] The provider still mirrors `openai-codex` metadata, and stream events still come back with the caller-facing provider id.\n    29\t- [ ] Root imports used by the current tests still resolve through the compatibility barrel.\n\n--- stage4 ---\n     1\t---\n     2\tplan_id: refactor-agnostic\n     3\ttitle: add non-pi validation and parity regression coverage\n     4\tstatus: idle\n     5\tupdated: 2026-04-14T00:00:00Z\n     6\t---\n     7\t\n     8\tProve the extracted core works without pi runtime imports, then finish the regression sweep by moving the remaining behavioral assertions into focused module tests.\n     9\t\n    10\t## Steps\n    11\t- [ ] Add one non-pi validation path that imports only `core/*` and exercises selection, refresh, caching, and quota handling with fake storage, fake token refresh, and fake usage fetch collaborators.\n    12\t- [ ] Keep the validation lightweight: a Vitest suite or small smoke harness is enough as long as it proves the core can be used without `@mariozechner/pi-coding-agent`.\n    13\t- [ ] Split the remaining assertions from `index.test.ts` into module-focused tests so root coverage can shrink to a compatibility smoke test.\n    14\t- [ ] Preserve the parity contract in tests for manual account precedence, usage parsing, untouched detection, cached usage refresh, token refresh threshold, quota-before-output rotation, and quota-after-output non-retry behavior.\n    15\t- [ ] Add or update README notes only as needed to explain the internal core/adapter split while keeping the public pi command surface unchanged.\n    16\t- [ ] Run the full validation matrix at the end of the rollout: `npm run lint`, `npm run tsgo`, and `npm run test`.\n    17\t\n    18\t## Success Criteria\n    19\t- [ ] At least one validation path imports the extracted core without pi runtime packages.\n    20\t- [ ] The regression suite covers the full behavior parity contract from the spec.\n    21\t- [ ] The root compatibility tests are reduced to a small smoke layer that proves the legacy exports and entrypoint still work.\n    22\t- [ ] The repository documentation still describes the same user-visible commands and behavior.\n    23\t- [ ] All checks pass.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776159440626},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_09e1a19d9e220e560169de0ad39910819a9a3b297390476d30\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp3grUlTQ7JNW466UJikDuUvrBzGUCd9kf0dQhGYcMKN6gqTokDu0bYD0vHUcjAXepeOcH5obMxihxdnfHhfnCxdhAE76lgU2vxbWwXl1-0ARpPomwQDYPnCYoqJNiWvYk01YdI1HjWJ0VnF5Rd9ofYSVasIttXYzcfgwz6vJyOFuCsdu76rsOxU7Z0yx4SQJdNl7I9Xnc_pmYaywB6ouSkwB9IrQNEZ7Zsr6VnEKXCYbNPs_4PwMa9r3SMeQJICUyVT4k7jTQWABrTRWqaxZ3MVkow4QtzF0-DEeNSkhBA6Byi-rv12kd1bOUgfL99DbCYimKLEMqQ3PjO_v_uk8nsxfdSbJjhgsDeSdk1k4VqDeF-eatCFSBDjU5eLmvtIJ7yQJzXQwhyYkGrWCk2jF2WWPwXG4jiw71ypmbigs8bGzC35HLpi55jbvecTSVaOUIvZ7pKwVw8R8UVIWUG_MAXOs3rGyL3iTuBBe2DqP3G-yf7elU88N6rwflY56_jlHynqVSGilC2tMtUDG9sdSM1mWrgJw7yj2IfysZ0FocayxfqfSkP5axikQjPo1ylBwQqDAd6py2AR0Q23vJozVR9iDZqfJ3kBMazV9__TQJfwGsfIz06v-62q4MuRfXIrC63cieBXTOLR3OOCAW4MwKt_e6NkbabsNxJTTkqnxUckMwv_gyZ96WBXUlK13tfeSh6sfVY_0XrUc1fv_qWeOdvGaHpst7QfXVOxkAfURAvO0YF8RmeRxJvP21DvNUjDFqtznT4c0UWmDSgVIOnbUWV7Sbuo8LqfFN-67TRn314gj30LQS5xwB3zmFcwri99ctte-dCpQVFZNe8S_dD9rsb-enNxJtfTioGRu_Ep5SMfauJymhNTOOQOs9qt64oCHFdBHDwhXaWuZdVr5mP-ve6lIlc0lKMJCnbkefmZKu9Bvmfhv3XjZ2Q5jJXgiILdZaCe5y\",\"summary\":[]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_cONHYDMz3p6T1RFAaGTscLDH|fc_09e1a19d9e220e560169de0ad47e2c819ab43d0ecb22887be1","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/linkdevk/repos/kg-multicodex && nl -ba .agents/tasks/refactor-agnostic/spec.md | sed -n '1,320p'","timeout":10},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"cd /home/linkdevk/repos/kg-multicodex && nl -ba .agents/tasks/refactor-agnostic/spec.md | sed -n '1,320p'\",\"timeout\":10}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":3474,"output":82,"cacheRead":44160,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":47716,"cost":{"input":0.008685,"output":0.00123,"cacheRead":0.01104,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.020955}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776159440629,"responseId":"resp_09e1a19d9e220e560169de0ad1959c819aa8eaa65430e14e67"},{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_cONHYDMz3p6T1RFAaGTscLDH|fc_09e1a19d9e220e560169de0ad47e2c819ab43d0ecb22887be1","toolName":"bash","content":[{"type":"text","text":"     1\t# Task Spec: refactor-agnostic\n     2\t\n     3\t## Objectives\n     4\t\n     5\t- Extract a **platform-agnostic multicodex-core** from the current monolithic `index.ts` so account state, selection, rotation policy, usage caching, and token refresh logic can be reused outside the pi extension runtime.\n     6\t- Keep the **pi adapter** thin: it should own commands, provider registration, UI prompts/notifications, browser-launch behavior, and stream/event translation.\n     7\t- Preserve current user-visible behavior and docs for the existing pi extension surface while enabling future non-pi consumers such as Mnemos bridges/gateways.\n     8\t- Create stable seams by **behavior**, not by arbitrary file size.\n     9\t\n    10\t## Non-goals\n    11\t\n    12\t- No change to the core Codex selection policy unless explicitly called out in tests and docs.\n    13\t- No redesign of the existing pi command UX in this task.\n    14\t- No gateway/server implementation in this task beyond interfaces or stubs that prove the core can be reused.\n    15\t- No migration to a new protocol or API surface for ChatGPT/Codex requests.\n    16\t- No broad package/workspace restructuring unless required to keep the core importable; the first pass should prefer module boundaries over repo re-layout.\n    17\t- In this first pass, `multicodex-core` and `multicodex-pi-adapter` refer to logical module boundaries inside the existing package unless a stronger packaging split is required by tests or distribution constraints.\n    18\t\n    19\t## Current-state analysis\n    20\t\n    21\t### Current repo state\n    22\t\n    23\t- The current repo root is effectively a **single entrypoint**: `index.ts` contains the whole behavior surface.\n    24\t- `index.test.ts` currently locks in the observed behavior for:\n    25\t  - quota error classification\n    26\t  - provider mirroring\n    27\t  - usage response parsing\n    28\t  - selection heuristics\n    29\t  - manual account preference in streaming\n    30\t  - quota-triggered rotation before any output\n    31\t- The current README exposes a very small public surface:\n    32\t  - `/multicodex-login`\n    33\t  - `/multicodex-use`\n    34\t  - `/multicodex-status`\n    35\t  - local dev install via `pi -e ./index.ts`\n    36\t- For this task, `/multicodex-use` is the canonical existing manual-switch command. Any rename such as `/multicodex-switch` is out of scope unless README, tests, and compatibility behavior are updated together.\n    37\t- The monolith couples together:\n    38\t  - filesystem persistence\n    39\t  - token refresh\n    40\t  - usage fetching\n    41\t  - selection policy\n    42\t  - provider registration\n    43\t  - stream retry/rotation\n    44\t  - browser login launch\n    45\t  - error message formatting\n    46\t\n    47\t### Reference implementation signal\n    48\t\n    49\tThe reference source under `.agents/sources/pi-multicodex/` already demonstrates a useful seam split:\n    50\t\n    51\t- `storage.ts`\n    52\t- `selection.ts`\n    53\t- `usage.ts`\n    54\t- `account-manager.ts`\n    55\t- `stream-wrapper.ts`\n    56\t- `provider.ts`\n    57\t- `commands.ts`\n    58\t- `hooks.ts`\n    59\t- `status.ts`\n    60\t- `auth.ts`\n    61\t- `usage-client.ts`\n    62\t- `refresh-race.test.ts`\n    63\t\n    64\tThat reference is **useful for boundaries**, but not all of its policy should be copied blindly:\n    65\t\n    66\t- the source has a richer command/status surface than the current README\n    67\t- the source has a lower-usage tie-breaker that is not currently part of the repo-root behavior contract\n    68\t- the source introduces pi-auth/imported-auth behaviors that are adapter-specific and should not leak into the platform-agnostic core\n    69\t\n    70\t### Current extraction problem\n    71\t\n    72\tThe current `index.ts` mixes three layers that should be separated:\n    73\t\n    74\t1. **pure domain logic**\n    75\t2. **storage / refresh orchestration**\n    76\t3. **pi runtime integration**\n    77\t\n    78\tThis makes it hard to reuse the account-selection and rotation logic in any non-pi context.\n    79\t\n    80\t## Behavior parity contract\n    81\t\n    82\tThis refactor must preserve the following behaviors unless a test and doc update explicitly changes them.\n    83\t\n    84\t### 1) Account selection\n    85\t\n    86\t- Manual account override wins when available.\n    87\t- Auto-selection excludes exhausted accounts.\n    88\t- Selection prefers accounts with **untouched** usage (`0%` in both windows) when available.\n    89\t- If no untouched account is available, selection should prefer the account with the earliest eligible weekly reset among the usable set.\n    90\t- If usage is unavailable for all candidates, fall back to a random available account.\n    91\t- Selection must honor an explicit `excludeEmails` set during retries.\n    92\t\n    93\t### 2) Usage parsing and refresh\n    94\t\n    95\t- Parse the `wham/usage` payload into a normalized snapshot with primary/secondary windows.\n    96\t- Convert `reset_at` seconds to millisecond timestamps.\n    97\t- Cache usage snapshots for **5 minutes** by default.\n    98\t- Retry transient usage fetch failures with bounded backoff.\n    99\t- Preserve the current retry policy: 2 retries, backoff roughly `300ms` then `900ms`.\n   100\t- Abort-like failures should not poison the cache path and should be treated as cancellations, not hard failures.\n   101\t\n   102\t### 3) Token refresh\n   103\t\n   104\t- Tokens are considered valid if they have at least 5 minutes of remaining life.\n   105\t- Expired tokens must be refreshed before use.\n   106\t- Successful refresh persists updated credentials back to managed storage.\n   107\t- Per-account refresh deduplication is a valid improvement for this task, but it is not part of the current monolith's proven behavior contract. If added, it must be treated as an intentional enhancement with dedicated tests.\n   108\t\n   109\t### 4) Quota/error rotation\n   110\t\n   111\t- A quota/rate-limit error before any streamed output should trigger account cooldown + rotation + retry.\n   112\t- Once any output has been forwarded, the stream must not silently rotate; it should forward the error and end.\n   113\t- The retry loop should remain bounded; do not create unbounded account cycling.\n   114\t- On quota hit, the failed account must be marked exhausted until its next reset time, or a fallback cooldown if no reset is known.\n   115\t\n   116\t### 5) Provider/adapter behavior\n   117\t\n   118\t- The provider must still mirror the underlying `openai-codex` model metadata.\n   119\t- The stream wrapper must still inject the selected account identifier into request headers.\n   120\t- The adapter must still rewrite provider metadata back to the caller-facing provider ID on events.\n   121\t- If the pi provider is unavailable, startup should warn/skip registration rather than crash.\n   122\t\n   123\t### 6) Public API compatibility\n   124\t\n   125\t- Keep existing root exports working during the transition, especially those used by current tests and external consumers.\n   126\t- If new core exports are introduced, the old names should remain available via a compatibility barrel until the migration is complete.\n   127\t\n   128\t## Target architecture\n   129\t\n   130\t### A) `multicodex-core`\n   131\t\n   132\tThe core boundary should be usable without pi extension runtime imports.\n   133\t\n   134\t#### Owns\n   135\t\n   136\t- account and storage models\n   137\t- account CRUD and active/manual resolution\n   138\t- selection policy and retry exclusion logic\n   139\t- token validity/refresh orchestration\n   140\t- usage snapshot cache and refresh policy\n   141\t- quota exhaustion and cooldown bookkeeping\n   142\t- state change notification hooks for adapters/UI\n   143\t- storage migration normalization and schema validation\n   144\t\n   145\t#### Must not own\n   146\t\n   147\t- pi command registration\n   148\t- pi UI notifications/prompts\n   149\t- browser-launch logic\n   150\t- provider mirroring / model registration\n   151\t- assistant message event shaping\n   152\t- any dependency on `@mariozechner/pi-coding-agent`\n   153\t\n   154\t#### Dependency model\n   155\t\n   156\tCore should accept injected collaborators rather than importing pi-specific APIs:\n   157\t\n   158\t- `StorageAdapter` for load/save\n   159\t- `TokenRefresher` for refresh-token exchange\n   160\t- `UsageClient` for usage fetches\n   161\t- `clock`/`random` overrides for deterministic testing\n   162\t- optional `logger`/`warning` callbacks for non-fatal diagnostics\n   163\t\n   164\t### B) `multicodex-pi-adapter`\n   165\t\n   166\tThe pi adapter boundary should be the only place that touches pi extension APIs.\n   167\t\n   168\t#### Owns\n   169\t\n   170\t- default extension export\n   171\t- `/multicodex-login`, `/multicodex-use`, `/multicodex-status` command wiring\n   172\t- provider registration for `openai-codex-responses`\n   173\t- stream bridging and retry/rotation orchestration for pi requests\n   174\t- UI prompts, selects, confirms, and notifications\n   175\t- browser-open behavior for the OAuth login flow\n   176\t- session hooks (`session_start`, `session_switch`, etc.)\n   177\t\n   178\t#### Must not own\n   179\t\n   180\t- account storage model rules\n   181\t- selection policy decisions\n   182\t- usage parsing logic\n   183\t- token refresh policy\n   184\t- quota bookkeeping policy\n   185\t\n   186\t### C) Optional gateway layer\n   187\t\n   188\tNot required for this task, but the core should be shaped so a future gateway can drive it with its own request protocol.\n   189\t\n   190\t- gateway should reuse the same selection/refresh/storage core\n   191\t- gateway should implement its own transport and streaming protocol\n   192\t- gateway should not need any pi-specific code\n   193\t\n   194\t## Module extraction map from current `index.ts`\n   195\t\n   196\t> This is the concrete first-pass map for splitting the current monolith by behavior seam.\n   197\t\n   198\t| Current region / functions | Target module | Notes |\n   199\t| --- | --- | --- |\n   200\t| `isQuotaErrorMessage`, `getErrorMessage`, `isAbortLikeError`, `getUsageHttpStatus`, `isRetryableUsageError`, `sleepWithSignal` | `core/errors.ts` and `core/retry.ts` | Keep retry classification pure and testable. |\n   201\t| `resolveCodexOAuthFns`, `loginOpenAICodexCompat`, `refreshOpenAICodexTokenCompat`, `openLoginInBrowser` | `adapter/pi/oauth.ts` and `adapter/pi/browser.ts` | pi-specific OAuth/browser integration stays out of core. |\n   202\t| `createErrorAssistantMessage`, `withProvider`, `createLinkedAbortController`, `createTimeoutController` | `adapter/pi/stream-utils.ts` | Event shaping and abort linking belong to the adapter. |\n   203\t| `normalizeUsedPercent`, `normalizeResetAt`, `parseUsageWindow`, `parseCodexUsageResponse`, `isUsageUntouched`, `getNextResetAt`, `getWeeklyResetAt` | `core/usage.ts` | Keep usage normalization and reset selection pure and platform-agnostic. |\n   204\t| `formatResetAt` | `adapter/pi/status.ts` (or adapter-local formatting module) | Human-readable status formatting is presentation logic and should stay out of core. |\n   205\t| `fetchCodexUsage` | `core/usage-client.ts` or injected `UsageClient` implementation | Core should own the default logic, but the HTTP client must be injectable. |\n   206\t| `Account`, `StorageData`, `isAccountAvailable`, `pickRandomAccount`, `pickEarliestWeeklyResetAccount`, `pickBestAccount` | `core/types.ts`, `core/selection.ts` | Selection is pure domain logic. |\n   207\t| `AccountManager` (load/save, cache, refresh, cooldown, active/manual state, refresh dedupe, token refresh, quota handling) | `core/account-manager.ts` | This is the main reusable runtime abstraction. |\n   208\t| `getOpenAICodexMirror`, `buildMulticodexProviderConfig` | `adapter/pi/provider.ts` | Mirror and provider registration are adapter-only. |\n   209\t| `multicodexExtension` default export | `adapter/pi/index.ts` | Root entrypoint remains the pi extension. |\n   210\t| `createStreamWrapper` | `adapter/pi/stream-wrapper.ts` | Keeps request rotation close to the provider bridge. |\n   211\t\n   212\t### Recommended file layout\n   213\t\n   214\t- `core/index.ts` â€” public core barrel\n   215\t- `core/types.ts`\n   216\t- `core/selection.ts`\n   217\t- `core/usage.ts`\n   218\t- `core/usage-client.ts`\n   219\t- `core/storage.ts`\n   220\t- `core/account-manager.ts`\n   221\t- `core/errors.ts`\n   222\t- `core/retry.ts`\n   223\t- `adapter/pi/index.ts`\n   224\t- `adapter/pi/provider.ts`\n   225\t- `adapter/pi/stream-wrapper.ts`\n   226\t- `adapter/pi/commands.ts`\n   227\t- `adapter/pi/hooks.ts`\n   228\t- `adapter/pi/status.ts`\n   229\t- `adapter/pi/oauth.ts`\n   230\t- `adapter/pi/browser.ts`\n   231\t- `adapter/pi/stream-utils.ts`\n   232\t- root `index.ts` as a compatibility barrel and default export shim during migration\n   233\t\n   234\t## Public interfaces\n   235\t\n   236\t### Root compatibility exports\n   237\t\n   238\tThe root `index.ts` compatibility barrel must continue to export the names that are exported today and used by the current tests:\n   239\t\n   240\t- `Account`\n   241\t- `AccountManager`\n   242\t- `CodexUsageSnapshot`\n   243\t- `ProviderModelDef`\n   244\t- `buildMulticodexProviderConfig`\n   245\t- `createStreamWrapper`\n   246\t- `getNextResetAt`\n   247\t- `getOpenAICodexMirror`\n   248\t- `getWeeklyResetAt`\n   249\t- `isQuotaErrorMessage`\n   250\t- `isUsageUntouched`\n   251\t- `parseCodexUsageResponse`\n   252\t- `pickBestAccount`\n   253\t- default export: the pi extension function\n   254\t\n   255\tNew core-only interfaces such as `StorageAdapter`, `UsageClient`, `TokenRefresher`, `StorageData`, or `createAccountManager` may be introduced, but they are not required to be root-stable in this task unless tests and docs are updated to make them public.\n   256\t\n   257\t### Core behavior surface required for adapter parity\n   258\t\n   259\tIf `AccountManager` remains a class, it must support the methods the current adapter behavior depends on:\n   260\t\n   261\t- `getAccounts()`\n   262\t- `getAccount(email)`\n   263\t- `getActiveAccount()`\n   264\t- `getManualAccount()`\n   265\t- `hasManualAccount()`\n   266\t- `getAvailableManualAccount(options?)`\n   267\t- `setActiveAccount(email)`\n   268\t- `setManualAccount(email)`\n   269\t- `clearManualAccount()`\n   270\t- `addOrUpdateAccount(email, creds)`\n   271\t- `getCachedUsage(email)`\n   272\t- `refreshUsageForAccount(account, options?)`\n   273\t- `refreshUsageForAllAccounts(options?)`\n   274\t- `refreshUsageIfStale(accounts, options?)`\n   275\t- `activateBestAccount(options?)`\n   276\t- `ensureValidToken(account)`\n   277\t- `handleQuotaExceeded(account, options?)`\n   278\t\n   279\tWarning and diagnostics behavior may remain an injected callback or small logger surface rather than requiring a broader `onStateChange(...)` API in this task.\n   280\t\n   281\t### Adapter exports\n   282\t\n   283\tKeep the following adapter exports available for tests and compatibility:\n   284\t\n   285\t- default export: the pi extension function\n   286\t- `buildMulticodexProviderConfig`\n   287\t- `createStreamWrapper`\n   288\t- `getOpenAICodexMirror`\n   289\t- `ProviderModelDef`\n   290\t\n   291\t## Storage and migration strategy\n   292\t\n   293\t### Canonical shape\n   294\t\n   295\tThe canonical storage shape should be versioned and stable:\n   296\t\n   297\t- `version`\n   298\t- `accounts[]`\n   299\t- `activeEmail?`\n   300\t- optional `$schema` metadata if the file format benefits from editor support\n   301\t\n   302\tAccount records should preserve:\n   303\t\n   304\t- `email`\n   305\t- `accessToken`\n   306\t- `refreshToken`\n   307\t- `expiresAt`\n   308\t- `accountId?`\n   309\t- `lastUsed?`\n   310\t- `quotaExhaustedUntil?`\n   311\t- `needsReauth?` if the core includes auth-failure tracking\n   312\t\n   313\t### Migration behavior\n   314\t\n   315\t- Treat storage migration as **additive and idempotent**.\n   316\t- Required compatibility input for this task is the current monolith's file at `~/.pi/agent/multicodex.json` with the legacy unversioned shape `{ accounts, activeEmail? }`.\n   317\t- The pi adapter owns the default file path; the core must receive storage through an injected adapter and must not hard-code the pi path.\n   318\t- Support for additional legacy shapes from the reference implementation is optional unless this task adds explicit fixtures and regression tests for them.\n   319\t- Corrupt-file salvage is optional scope; if implemented, the spec/tests must define exactly which fields are salvageable and what happens to malformed records.\n   320\t- On successful load of a supported legacy file, write back the canonical versioned format.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776159445093},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_09e1a19d9e220e560169de0ad6f09c819ab828b690de04eb4a\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp3grYWFwnpSY7zTukojQWhxxyaP89zDsVnqOrYByl6AsuV9EOEqADiAUkXYpUya5CmTwUpiu61pBTO_qb7l2qbGGGYBR7YYOWKV9s2Pc31GRcGTmwXd3wfT2EJKivkGRPIQqGj7DryLX5N0fUG_xHMq7nb3wBVXKn3aOHSQIBC5p4WkT6YI-N9RfRd-CA351rHvEGzRozSH92fHUi2b5aUlREqcSPvp0cA4fqAl6kIyIdFWPPwoC02uBtP3z7r5j