x_retro","arguments":{"slug":"kg-multicodex-refactor-plan-must-pin-rotation-and-refresh-contracts","title":"refactor plan parity traps","body":"In `kg-multicodex`, a refactor plan can look architecture-aligned while still missing critical behavior contracts unless the stage success criteria name them explicitly. The current `refactor-agnostic` plan matches the [[multicodex-core]]/[[multicodex-pi-adapter]] boundary and phase order, but it still needs explicit coverage for the `excludeEmails` retry path, selected-account header injection, startup warn/skip behavior, session-hook parity, and especially the max-5 stream rotation bound. The plan also treats token refresh deduplication as optional even though the specâ€™s later error-semantics/testing sections effectively require one in-flight refresh per account.","category":"architecture"},"partialJson":"{\"slug\":\"kg-multicodex-refactor-plan-must-pin-rotation-and-refresh-contracts\",\"title\":\"refactor plan parity traps\",\"body\":\"In `kg-multicodex`, a refactor plan can look architecture-aligned while still missing critical behavior contracts unless the stage success criteria name them explicitly. The current `refactor-agnostic` plan matches the [[multicodex-core]]/[[multicodex-pi-adapter]] boundary and phase order, but it still needs explicit coverage for the `excludeEmails` retry path, selected-account header injection, startup warn/skip behavior, session-hook parity, and especially the max-5 stream rotation bound. The plan also treats token refresh deduplication as optional even though the specâ€™s later error-semantics/testing sections effectively require one in-flight refresh per account.\",\"category\":\"architecture\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":28099,"output":502,"cacheRead":27904,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":56505,"cost":{"input":0.0702475,"output":0.00753,"cacheRead":0.0069759999999999996,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0847535}},"stopReason":"t